  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the visions that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah
        and Jerusalem. He saw these visions during the years when Uzziah, Jotham,
        Ahaz, and Hezekiah were kings of Judah.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'These kings reigned from 792 to 686 '
          body: 
    - title: A Message for Rebellious Judah
      content: "Listen, O heavens! Pay attention, earth!\n\tThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201CThe children I raised and cared for\n\thave rebelled against
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even an ox knows its owner,\n\tand a donkey recognizes its master\u2019s
        care\u2014\n\tbut Israel doesn\u2019t know its master.\n\tMy people don\u2019t
        recognize my care for them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, what a sinful nation they are\u2014\n\tloaded down with a burden
        of guilt.\n\tThey are evil people,\n\tcorrupt children who have rejected
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThey have despised the Holy One of
        Israel\n\tand turned their backs on him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do you continue to invite punishment?\n\tMust you rebel forever?\n\tYour
        head is injured,\n\tand your heart is sick.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are battered from head to foot\u2014\n\tcovered with bruises,
        welts, and infected wounds\u2014\n\twithout any soothing ointments or bandages.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your country lies in ruins,\n\tand your towns are burned.\n\tForeigners
        plunder your fields before your eyes\n\tand destroy everything they see.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Beautiful Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]] stands abandoned\n\tlike a watchman\u2019s
        shelter in a vineyard,\n\tlike a lean-to in a cucumber field after the harvest,\n\tlike
        a helpless city under siege.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: The daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\thad
        not spared a few of us,[COMMENT[0]]we would have been wiped out like Sodom,\n\tdestroyed
        like Gomorrah.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'a few of our children. '
        - ft: Compare Rom 9:29.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you leaders of \u201CSodom.\u201D\n\tListen
        to the law of our God, people of \u201CGomorrah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat makes you think I want all your sacrifices?\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI am sick of your burnt offerings
        of rams\n\tand the fat of fattened cattle.\n\tI get no pleasure from the
        blood\n\tof bulls and lambs and goats.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you come to worship me,\n\twho asked you to parade through my
        courts with all your ceremony?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stop bringing me your meaningless gifts;\n\tthe incense of your offerings
        disgusts me!\n\tAs for your celebrations of the new moon and the Sabbath\n\tand
        your special days for fasting\u2014\n\tthey are all sinful and false.\n\tI
        want no more of your pious meetings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I hate your new moon celebrations and your annual festivals.\n\tThey
        are a burden to me. I cannot stand them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you lift up your hands in prayer, I will not look.\n\tThough
        you offer many prayers, I will not listen,\n\tfor your hands are covered
        with the blood of innocent victims.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wash yourselves and be clean!\n\tGet your sins out of my sight.\n\tGive
        up your evil ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Learn to do good.\n\tSeek justice.\n\tHelp the oppressed.\n\tDefend
        the cause of orphans.\n\tFight for the rights of widows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome now, let\u2019s settle this,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CThough
        your sins are like scarlet,\n\tI will make them as white as snow.\n\tThough
        they are red like crimson,\n\tI will make them as white as wool.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you will only obey me,\n\tyou will have plenty to eat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you turn away and refuse to listen,\n\tyou will be devoured
        by the sword of your enemies.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Unfaithful Jerusalem
      content: "See how Jerusalem, once so faithful,\n\thas become a prostitute.\n\tOnce
        the home of justice and righteousness,\n\tshe is now filled with murderers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Once like pure silver,\n\tyou have become like worthless slag.\n\tOnce
        so pure,\n\tyou are now like watered-down wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your leaders are rebels,\n\tthe companions of thieves.\n\tAll of
        them love bribes\n\tand demand payoffs,\n\tbut they refuse to defend the
        cause of orphans\n\tor fight for the rights of widows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\tthe Mighty One of Israel, says,\n\t\u201CI will take revenge on
        my enemies\n\tand pay back my foes!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will raise my fist against you.\n\tI will melt you down and skim
        off your slag.\n\tI will remove all your impurities.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will give you good judges again\n\tand wise counselors like
        you used to have.\n\tThen Jerusalem will again be called the Home of Justice\n\tand
        the Faithful City.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Zion will be restored by justice;\n\tthose who repent will be revived
        by righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But rebels and sinners will be completely destroyed,\n\tand those
        who desert the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be consumed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be ashamed of your idol worship\n\tin groves of sacred oaks.\n\tYou
        will blush because you worshiped\n\tin gardens dedicated to idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be like a great tree with withered leaves,\n\tlike a garden
        without water.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The strongest among you will disappear like straw;\n\ttheir evil
        deeds will be the spark that sets it on fire.\n\tThey and their evil works
        will burn up together,\n\tand no one will be able to put out the fire."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Future Reign"
      content: 'This is a vision that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and
        Jerusalem:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the last days, the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        house\n\twill be the highest of all\u2014\n\tthe most important place on
        earth.\n\tIt will be raised above the other hills,\n\tand people from all
        over the world will stream there to worship.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People from many nations will come and say,\n\t\u201CCome, let us
        go up to the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tto the house
        of Jacob\u2019s God.\n\tThere he will teach us his ways,\n\tand we will walk
        in his paths.\u201D\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s teaching
        will go out from Zion;\n\this word will go out from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will mediate between nations\n\tand
        will settle international disputes.\n\tThey will hammer their swords into
        plowshares\n\tand their spears into pruning hooks.\n\tNation will no longer
        fight against nation,\n\tnor train for war anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning of Judgment
      content: "Come, descendants of Jacob,\n\tlet us walk in the light of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected his people,\n\tthe
        descendants of Jacob,\n\tbecause they have filled their land with practices
        from the East\n\tand with sorcerers, as the Philistines do.\n\tThey have
        made alliances with pagans.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Israel is full of silver and gold;\n\tthere is no end to its treasures.\n\tTheir
        land is full of warhorses;\n\tthere is no end to its chariots.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their land is full of idols;\n\tthe people worship things they have
        made\n\twith their own hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now they will be humbled,\n\tand all will be brought low\u2014\n\tdo
        not forgive them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Crawl into caves in the rocks.\n\tHide in the dust\n\tfrom the terror
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand the glory of his majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Human pride will be brought down,\n\tand human arrogance will be
        humbled.\n\tOnly the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be exalted\n\ton that
        day of judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\thas
        a day of reckoning.\n\tHe will punish the proud and mighty\n\tand bring down
        everything that is exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will cut down the tall cedars of Lebanon\n\tand all the mighty
        oaks of Bashan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will level all the high mountains\n\tand all the lofty hills.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will break down every high tower\n\tand every fortified wall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will destroy all the great trading ships[COMMENT[0]]and every
        magnificent vessel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: every ship of Tarshish.
    - title: 
      content: "Human pride will be humbled,\n\tand human arrogance will be brought
        down.\n\tOnly the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be exalted\n\ton that
        day of judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Idols will completely disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises to shake the earth,\n\this
        enemies will crawl into holes in the ground.\n\tThey will hide in caves in
        the rocks\n\tfrom the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand the
        glory of his majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On that day of judgment they will abandon the gold and silver idols\n\tthey
        made for themselves to worship.\n\tThey will leave their gods to the rodents
        and bats,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "while they crawl away into caverns\n\tand hide among the jagged rocks
        in the cliffs.\n\tThey will try to escape the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand
        the glory of his majesty\n\tas he rises to shake the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t put your trust in mere humans.\n\tThey are as frail as
        breath.\n\tWhat good are they?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment against Judah
      content: "The Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\twill
        take away from Jerusalem and Judah\n\teverything they depend on:\n\tevery
        bit of bread\n\tand every drop of water,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "all their heroes and soldiers,\n\tjudges and prophets,\n\tfortune-tellers
        and elders,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "army officers and high officials,\n\tadvisers, skilled sorcerers,
        and astrologers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make boys their leaders,\n\tand toddlers their rulers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People will oppress each other\u2014\n\tman against man,\n\tneighbor
        against neighbor.\n\tYoung people will insult their elders,\n\tand vulgar
        people will sneer at the honorable.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In those days a man will say to his brother,\n\t\u201CSince you have
        a coat, you be our leader!\n\tTake charge of this heap of ruins!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he will reply,\n\t\u201CNo! I can\u2019t help.\n\tI don\u2019t
        have any extra food or clothes.\n\tDon\u2019t put me in charge!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For Jerusalem will stumble,\n\tand Judah will fall,\n\tbecause they
        speak out against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and refuse to obey him.\n\tThey
        provoke him to his face.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The very look on their faces gives them away.\n\tThey display their
        sin like the people of Sodom\n\tand don\u2019t even try to hide it.\n\tThey
        are doomed!\n\tThey have brought destruction upon themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell the godly that all will be well for them.\n\tThey will enjoy
        the rich reward they have earned!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the wicked are doomed,\n\tfor they will get exactly what they
        deserve.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Childish leaders oppress my people,\n\tand women rule over them.\n\tO
        my people, your leaders mislead you;\n\tthey send you down the wrong road.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes his place in court\n\tand presents
        his case against his people.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: against the peoples.
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>\n\tcomes forward to pronounce judgment\n\ton
        the elders and rulers of his people:\n\t\u201CYou have ruined Israel, my
        vineyard.\n\tYour houses are filled with things stolen from the poor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How dare you crush my people,\n\tgrinding the faces of the poor into
        the dust?\u201D\n\tdemands the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning to Jerusalem
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CBeautiful Zion[COMMENT[0]]
        is haughty:\n\tcraning her elegant neck,\n\tflirting with her eyes,\n\twalking
        with dainty steps,\n\ttinkling her ankle bracelets.  "
