    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow for those who get up early in the morning\n\tlooking
        for a drink of alcohol\n\tand spend long evenings drinking wine\n\tto make
        themselves flaming drunk.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They furnish wine and lovely music at their grand parties\u2014\n\tlyre
        and harp, tambourine and flute\u2014\n\tbut they never think about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tor
        notice what he is doing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So my people will go into exile far away\n\tbecause they do not know
        me.\n\tThose who are great and honored will starve,\n\tand the common people
        will die of thirst.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The grave[COMMENT[0]] is licking its lips in anticipation,\n\topening
        its mouth wide.\n\tThe great and the lowly\n\tand all the drunken mob will
        be swallowed up.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "Humanity will be destroyed, and people brought down;\n\teven the
        arrogant will lower their eyes in humiliation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will
        be exalted by his justice.\n\tThe holiness of God will be displayed by his
        righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day lambs will find good pastures,\n\tand fattened sheep
        and young goats[COMMENT[0]] will feed among the ruins.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: and strangers.
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow for those who drag their sins behind them\n\twith ropes
        made of lies,\n\twho drag wickedness behind them like a cart!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They even mock God and say,\n\t\u201CHurry up and do something!\n\tWe
        want to see what you can do.\n\tLet the Holy One of Israel carry out his
        plan,\n\tfor we want to know what it is.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow for those who say\n\tthat evil is good and good is evil,\n\tthat
        dark is light and light is dark,\n\tthat bitter is sweet and sweet is bitter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow for those who are wise in their own eyes\n\tand think
        themselves so clever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow for those who are heroes at drinking wine\n\tand boast
        about all the alcohol they can hold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They take bribes to let the wicked go free,\n\tand they punish the
        innocent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, just as fire licks up stubble\n\tand dry grass shrivels
        in the flame,\n\tso their roots will rot\n\tand their flowers wither.\n\tFor
        they have rejected the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies;\n\tthey have despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger burns
        against his people,\n\tand why he has raised his fist to crush them.\n\tThe
        mountains tremble,\n\tand the corpses of his people litter the streets like
        garbage.\n\tBut even then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger
        is not satisfied.\n\tHis fist is still poised to strike!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will send a signal to distant nations far away\n\tand whistle
        to those at the ends of the earth.\n\tThey will come racing toward Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will not get tired or stumble.\n\tThey will not stop for rest
        or sleep.\n\tNot a belt will be loose,\n\tnot a sandal strap broken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their arrows will be sharp\n\tand their bows ready for battle.\n\tSparks
        will fly from their horses\u2019 hooves,\n\tand the wheels of their chariots
        will spin like a whirlwind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will roar like lions,\n\tlike the strongest of lions.\n\tGrowling,
        they will pounce on their victims and carry them off,\n\tand no one will
        be there to rescue them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will roar over their victims on that day of destruction\n\tlike
        the roaring of the sea.\n\tIf someone looks across the land,\n\tonly darkness
        and distress will be seen;\n\teven the light will be darkened by clouds."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Isaiah\u2019s Cleansing and Call"
      content: 'It was in the year King Uzziah died[COMMENT[0]] that I saw the Lord.
        He was sitting on a lofty throne, and the train of his robe filled the Temple. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'King Uzziah died in 740 '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Attending him were mighty seraphim, each having six wings. With two
        wings they covered their faces, with two they covered their feet, and with
        two they flew. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were calling out to each other,\n\t\u201CHoly, holy, holy is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies!\n\tThe whole earth
        is filled with his glory!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their voices shook the Temple to its foundations, and the entire
        building was filled with smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CIt\u2019s all over! I am doomed, for I am a sinful
        man. I have filthy lips, and I live among a people with filthy lips. Yet
        I have seen the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then one of the seraphim flew to me with a burning coal he had taken
        from the altar with a pair of tongs. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He touched my lips with it and said, \u201CSee, this coal has touched
        your lips. Now your guilt is removed, and your sins are forgiven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard the Lord asking, \u201CWhom should I send as a messenger
        to this people? Who will go for us?\u201D\n\tI said, \u201CHere I am. Send
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he said, \u201CYes, go, and say to this people,\n\t\u2018Listen
        carefully, but do not understand.\n\tWatch closely, but learn nothing.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Harden the hearts of these people.\n\tPlug their ears and shut their
        eyes.\n\tThat way, they will not see with their eyes,\n\tnor hear with their
        ears,\n\tnor understand with their hearts\n\tand turn to me for healing.\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:9-10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: "And he said, \u201CGo and say to this people, / \u2018When you hear
            what I say, you will not understand. / When you see what I do, you will
            not comprehend.\u2019 / For the hearts of these people are hardened,
            / and their ears cannot hear, and they have closed their eyes\u2014 /
            so their eyes cannot see, / and their ears cannot hear, / and their hearts
            cannot understand, / and they cannot turn to me and let me heal them.\u201D "
        - ft: Compare Matt 13:14-15; Mark 4:12; Luke 8:10; Acts 28:26-27.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CLord, how long will this go on?\u201D\n\tAnd he
        replied,\n\t\u201CUntil their towns are empty,\n\ttheir houses are deserted,\n\tand
        the whole country is a wasteland;  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent everyone away,\n\tand
        the entire land of Israel lies deserted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If even a tenth\u2014a remnant\u2014survive,\n\tit will be invaded
        again and burned.\n\tBut as a terebinth or oak tree leaves a stump when it
        is cut down,\n\tso Israel\u2019s stump will be a holy seed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message for Ahaz
      content: 'When Ahaz, son of Jotham and grandson of Uzziah, was king of Judah,
        King Rezin of Syria[COMMENT[0]] and Pekah son of Remaliah, the king of Israel,
        set out to attack Jerusalem. However, they were unable to carry out their
        plan.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Aram; '
        - ft: also in 7:2, 4, 5, 8.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The news had come to the royal court of Judah: \u201CSyria is allied
        with Israel[COMMENT[0]] against us!\u201D So the hearts of the king and his
        people trembled with fear, like trees shaking in a storm.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel; also in 7:5, 8, 9, 17.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Isaiah, \u201CTake your
        son Shear-jashub[COMMENT[0]] and go out to meet King Ahaz. You will find
        him at the end of the aqueduct that feeds water into the upper pool, near
        the road leading to the field where cloth is washed.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3a '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Shear-jashub '
        - ft: "means \u201CA remnant will return.\u201D"
          body: 
      - number: '7:3b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: bleached.
    - title: 
      content: "Tell him to stop worrying. Tell him he doesn\u2019t need to fear
        the fierce anger of those two burned-out embers, King Rezin of Syria and
        Pekah son of Remaliah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the kings of Syria and Israel are plotting against him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018We will attack Judah and capture it for ourselves. Then we
        will install the son of Tabeel as Judah\u2019s king.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThis
        invasion will never happen;\n\tit will never take place;  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for Syria is no stronger than its capital, Damascus,\n\tand Damascus
        is no stronger than its king, Rezin.\n\tAs for Israel, within sixty-five
        years\n\tit will be crushed and completely destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Israel is no stronger than its capital, Samaria,\n\tand Samaria is
        no stronger than its king, Pekah son of Remaliah.\n\tUnless your faith is
        firm,\n\tI cannot make you stand firm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Sign of Immanuel
      content: 'Later, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent this message to King
        Ahaz: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAsk the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God for a sign of
        confirmation, Ahaz. Make it as difficult as you want\u2014as high as heaven
        or as deep as the place of the dead.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: as deep as Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "But the king refused. \u201CNo,\u201D he said, \u201CI will not test
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> like that.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CListen well, you royal family of David! Isn\u2019t
        it enough to exhaust human patience? Must you exhaust the patience of my
        God as well? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All right then, the Lord himself will give you the sign. Look! The
        virgin[COMMENT[0]] will conceive a child! She will give birth to a son and
        will call him Immanuel (which means \u2018God is with us\u2019). "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: young woman.
    - title: 
      content: 'By the time this child is old enough to choose what is right and
        reject what is wrong, he will be eating yogurt[COMMENT[0]] and honey. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'curds; '
        - ft: also in 7:22.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For before the child is that old, the lands of the two kings you
        fear so much will both be deserted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring things on you,
        your nation, and your family unlike anything since Israel broke away from
        Judah. He will bring the king of Assyria upon you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will whistle for the
        army of southern Egypt and for the army of Assyria. They will swarm around
        you like flies and bees. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will come in vast hordes and settle in the fertile areas and
        also in the desolate valleys, caves, and thorny places. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the Lord will hire a \u201Crazor\u201D from beyond the
        Euphrates River[COMMENT[0]]\u2014the king of Assyria\u2014and use it to shave
        off everything: your land, your crops, and your people.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:20a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the river.
      - number: '7:20b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: shave off the head, the hair of the legs, and the beard.
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day a farmer will be fortunate to have a cow and two sheep
        or goats left. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nevertheless, there will be enough milk for everyone because so few
        people will be left in the land. They will eat their fill of yogurt and honey. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the lush vineyards, now worth 1,000 pieces of silver,[COMMENT[0]]
        will become patches of briers and thorns. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1,000 [shekels] of silver, '
        - ft: about 25 pounds or 11.4 kilograms in weight.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'The entire land will become a vast expanse of briers and thorns,
        a hunting ground overrun by wildlife. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: No one will go to the fertile hillsides where the gardens once grew,
        for briers and thorns will cover them. Cattle, sheep, and goats will graze
        there.
