    - title: 
      content: "We destroyed Calno just as we did Carchemish.\n\tHamath fell before
        us as Arpad did.\n\tAnd we destroyed Samaria just as we did Damascus.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, we have finished off many a kingdom\n\twhose gods were greater
        than those in Jerusalem and Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So we will defeat Jerusalem and her gods,\n\tjust as we destroyed
        Samaria with hers.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the Lord has used the king of Assyria to accomplish his purposes
        on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem, he will turn against the king of Assyria
        and punish him\u2014for he is proud and arrogant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He boasts,\n\t\u201CBy my own powerful arm I have done this.\n\tWith
        my own shrewd wisdom I planned it.\n\tI have broken down the defenses of
        nations\n\tand carried off their treasures.\n\tI have knocked down their
        kings like a bull.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have robbed their nests of riches\n\tand gathered up kingdoms as
        a farmer gathers eggs.\n\tNo one can even flap a wing against me\n\tor utter
        a peep of protest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But can the ax boast greater power than the person who uses it?\n\tIs
        the saw greater than the person who saws?\n\tCan a rod strike unless a hand
        moves it?\n\tCan a wooden cane walk by itself?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\twill send a plague among Assyria\u2019s proud troops,\n\tand a
        flaming fire will consume its glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the Light of Israel, will be
        a fire;\n\tthe Holy One will be a flame.\n\tHe will devour the thorns and
        briers with fire,\n\tburning up the enemy in a single night.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will consume Assyria\u2019s glory\n\tlike
        a fire consumes a forest in a fruitful land;\n\tit will waste away like sick
        people in a plague.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Of all that glorious forest, only a few trees will survive\u2014\n\tso
        few that a child could count them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s People"
      content: "In that day the remnant left in Israel,\n\tthe survivors in the house
        of Jacob,\n\twill no longer depend on allies\n\twho seek to destroy them.\n\tBut
        they will faithfully trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe Holy
        One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A remnant will return;[COMMENT[0]]yes, the remnant of Jacob will
        return to the Mighty God.  '
