  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Babylon
      content: 'Isaiah son of Amoz received this message concerning the destruction
        of Babylon:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRaise a signal flag on a bare hilltop.\n\tCall up an army against
        Babylon.\n\tWave your hand to encourage them\n\tas they march into the palaces
        of the high and mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have dedicated these soldiers
        for this task.\n\tYes, I have called mighty warriors to express my anger,\n\tand
        they will rejoice when I am exalted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the noise on the mountains!\n\tListen, as the vast armies march!\n\tIt
        is the noise and shouting of many nations.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies has called this army together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They come from distant countries,\n\tfrom beyond the farthest horizons.\n\tThey
        are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s weapons to carry out his anger.\n\tWith
        them he will destroy the whole land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Scream in terror, for the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has arrived\u2014\n\tthe time for the Almighty to destroy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Every arm is paralyzed with fear.\n\tEvery heart melts,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and people are terrified.\n\tPangs of anguish grip them,\n\tlike
        those of a woman in labor.\n\tThey look helplessly at one another,\n\ttheir
        faces aflame with fear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For see, the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming\u2014\n\tthe
        terrible day of his fury and fierce anger.\n\tThe land will be made desolate,\n\tand
        all the sinners destroyed with it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The heavens will be black above them;\n\tthe stars will give no light.\n\tThe
        sun will be dark when it rises,\n\tand the moon will provide no light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, will punish the world
        for its evil\n\tand the wicked for their sin.\n\tI will crush the arrogance
        of the proud\n\tand humble the pride of the mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make people scarcer than gold\u2014\n\tmore rare than the
        fine gold of Ophir.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will shake the heavens.\n\tThe earth will move from its place\n\twhen
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies displays his wrath\n\tin
        the day of his fierce anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone in Babylon will run about like a hunted gazelle,\n\tlike
        sheep without a shepherd.\n\tThey will try to find their own people\n\tand
        flee to their own land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who is captured will be cut down\u2014\n\trun through with
        a sword.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their little children will be dashed to death before their eyes.\n\tTheir
        homes will be sacked, and their wives will be raped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I will stir up the Medes against Babylon.\n\tThey cannot
        be tempted by silver\n\tor bribed with gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The attacking armies will shoot down the young men with arrows.\n\tThey
        will have no mercy on helpless babies\n\tand will show no compassion for
        children.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Babylon, the most glorious of kingdoms,\n\tthe flower of Chaldean
        pride,\n\twill be devastated like Sodom and Gomorrah\n\twhen God destroyed
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Babylon will never be inhabited again.\n\tIt will remain empty for
        generation after generation.\n\tNomads will refuse to camp there,\n\tand
        shepherds will not bed down their sheep.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Desert animals will move into the ruined city,\n\tand the houses
        will be haunted by howling creatures.\n\tOwls will live among the ruins,\n\tand
        wild goats will go there to dance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hyenas will howl in its fortresses,\n\tand jackals will make dens
        in its luxurious palaces.\n\tBabylon\u2019s days are numbered;\n\tits time
        of destruction will soon arrive."
      comments: []
