  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Moab
      content: "This message came to me concerning Moab:\n\tIn one night the town
        of Ar will be leveled,\n\tand the city of Kir will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your people will go to their temple in Dibon to mourn.\n\tThey will
        go to their sacred shrines to weep.\n\tThey will wail for the fate of Nebo
        and Medeba,\n\tshaving their heads in sorrow and cutting off their beards.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will wear burlap as they wander the streets.\n\tFrom every home
        and public square will come the sound of wailing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Heshbon and Elealeh will cry out;\n\ttheir voices will
        be heard as far away as Jahaz!\n\tThe bravest warriors of Moab will cry out
        in utter terror.\n\tThey will be helpless with fear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My heart weeps for Moab.\n\tIts people flee to Zoar and Eglath-shelishiyah.\n\tWeeping,
        they climb the road to Luhith.\n\tTheir cries of distress can be heard all
        along the road to Horonaim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the waters of Nimrim are dried up!\n\tThe grassy banks are scorched.\n\tThe
        tender plants are gone;\n\tnothing green remains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people grab their possessions\n\tand carry them across the Ravine
        of Willows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A cry of distress echoes through the land of Moab\n\tfrom one end
        to the other\u2014\n\tfrom Eglaim to Beer-elim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The stream near Dibon[COMMENT[0]] runs red with blood,\n\tbut I am
        still not finished with Dibon!\n\tLions will hunt down the survivors\u2014\n\tboth
        those who try to escape\n\tand those who remain behind."
      comments:
      - number: '15:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls, some Greek manuscripts, and Latin Vulgate;
            Masoretic Text reads '
          body: 'Dimon; '
        - ft: also in 15:9b.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Send lambs from Sela as tribute\n\tto the ruler of the land.\n\tSend
        them through the desert\n\tto the mountain of beautiful Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The women of Moab are left like homeless birds\n\tat the shallow
        crossings of the Arnon River.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHelp us,\u201D they cry.\n\t\u201CDefend us against our enemies.\n\tProtect
        us from their relentless attack.\n\tDo not betray us now that we have escaped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let our refugees stay among you.\n\tHide them from our enemies until
        the terror is past.\u201D\n\tWhen oppression and destruction have ended\n\tand
        enemy raiders have disappeared,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then God will establish one of David\u2019s descendants as king.\n\tHe
        will rule with mercy and truth.\n\tHe will always do what is just\n\tand
        be eager to do what is right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We have heard about proud Moab\u2014\n\tabout its pride and arrogance
        and rage.\n\tBut all that boasting has disappeared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The entire land of Moab weeps.\n\tYes, everyone in Moab mourns\n\tfor
        the cakes of raisins from Kir-hareseth.\n\tThey are all gone now.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The farms of Heshbon are abandoned;\n\tthe vineyards at Sibmah are
        deserted.\n\tThe rulers of the nations have broken down Moab\u2014\n\tthat
        beautiful grapevine.\n\tIts tendrils spread north as far as the town of Jazer\n\tand
        trailed eastward into the wilderness.\n\tIts shoots reached so far west\n\tthat
        they crossed over the Dead Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the sea.
    - title: 
      content: "So now I weep for Jazer and the vineyards of Sibmah;\n\tmy tears
        will flow for Heshbon and Elealeh.\n\tThere are no more shouts of joy\n\tover
        your summer fruits and harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gone now is the gladness,\n\tgone the joy of harvest.\n\tThere will
        be no singing in the vineyards,\n\tno more happy shouts,\n\tno treading of
        grapes in the winepresses.\n\tI have ended all their harvest joys.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My heart\u2019s cry for Moab is like a lament on a harp.\n\tI am
        filled with anguish for Kir-hareseth.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Kir-heres, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Kir-hareseth.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Moab will worship at their pagan shrines,\n\tbut it
        will do them no good.\n\tThey will cry to the gods in their temples,\n\tbut
        no one will be able to save them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has already said these things about
        Moab in the past. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CWithin three
        years, counting each day,[COMMENT[0]] the glory of Moab will be ended. From
        its great population, only a feeble few will be left alive.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Within three years, as a servant bound by contract would count them.
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Damascus and Israel
      content: "This message came to me concerning Damascus:\n\t\u201CLook, the city
        of Damascus will disappear!\n\tIt will become a heap of ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The towns of Aroer will be deserted.\n\tFlocks will graze in the
        streets and lie down undisturbed,\n\twith no one to chase them away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The fortified towns of Israel[COMMENT[0]] will also be destroyed,\n\tand
        the royal power of Damascus will end.\n\tAll that remains of Syria[COMMENT[1]]will
        share the fate of Israel\u2019s departed glory,\u201D\n\tdeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:3a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
          body: 
      - number: '17:3b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Aram.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day Israel\u2019s[COMMENT[0]] glory will grow dim;\n\tits
        robust body will waste away.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "Jacob\u2019s. "
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The whole land will look like a grainfield\n\tafter the harvesters
        have gathered the grain.\n\tIt will be desolate,\n\tlike the fields in the
        valley of Rephaim after the harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Only a few of its people will be left,\n\tlike stray olives left
        on a tree after the harvest.\n\tOnly two or three remain in the highest branches,\n\tfour
        or five scattered here and there on the limbs,\u201D\n\tdeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then at last the people will look to their Creator\n\tand turn their
        eyes to the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will no longer look to their idols for help\n\tor worship what
        their own hands have made.\n\tThey will never again bow down to their Asherah
        poles\n\tor worship at the pagan shrines they have built.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their largest cities will be like a deserted forest,\n\tlike the
        land the Hivites and Amorites abandoned[COMMENT[0]]when the Israelites came
        here so long ago.\n\tIt will be utterly desolate.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: like places of the wood and the highest bough.
    - title: 
      content: "Why? Because you have turned from the God who can save you.\n\tYou
        have forgotten the Rock who can hide you.\n\tSo you may plant the finest
        grapevines\n\tand import the most expensive seedlings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They may sprout on the day you set them out;\n\tyes, they may blossom
        on the very morning you plant them,\n\tbut you will never pick any grapes
        from them.\n\tYour only harvest will be a load of grief and unrelieved pain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen! The armies of many nations\n\troar like the roaring of the
        sea.\n\tHear the thunder of the mighty forces\n\tas they rush forward like
        thundering waves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But though they thunder like breakers on a beach,\n\tGod will silence
        them, and they will run away.\n\tThey will flee like chaff scattered by the
        wind,\n\tlike a tumbleweed whirling before a storm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the evening Israel waits in terror,\n\tbut by dawn its enemies
        are dead.\n\tThis is the just reward of those who plunder us,\n\ta fitting
        end for those who destroy us."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Ethiopia
      content: "Listen, Ethiopia[COMMENT[0]]\u2014land of fluttering sails[COMMENT[1]]that
        lies at the headwaters of the Nile,  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Cush.
      - number: '18:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'land of many locusts; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: land of whirring wings.
    - title: 
      content: "that sends ambassadors\n\tin swift boats down the river.\n\tGo, swift
        messengers!\n\tTake a message to a tall, smooth-skinned people,\n\twho are
        feared far and wide\n\tfor their conquests and destruction,\n\tand whose
        land is divided by rivers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All you people of the world,\n\teveryone who lives on the earth\u2014\n\twhen
        I raise my battle flag on the mountain, look!\n\tWhen I blow the ram\u2019s
        horn, listen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told me this:\n\t\u201CI
        will watch quietly from my dwelling place\u2014\n\tas quietly as the heat
        rises on a summer day,\n\tor as the morning dew forms during the harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even before you begin your attack,\n\twhile your plans are ripening
        like grapes,\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cut off your new growth
        with pruning shears.\n\tHe will snip off and discard your spreading branches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your mighty army will be left dead in the fields\n\tfor the mountain
        vultures and wild animals.\n\tThe vultures will tear at the corpses all summer.\n\tThe
        wild animals will gnaw at the bones all winter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        will receive gifts\n\tfrom this land divided by rivers,\n\tfrom this tall,
        smooth-skinned people,\n\twho are feared far and wide for their conquests
        and destruction.\n\tThey will bring the gifts to Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]]where
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies dwells."
      comments:
      - number: '18:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Mount Zion.
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Egypt
      content: "This message came to me concerning Egypt:\n\tLook! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is advancing against Egypt,\n\triding on a swift cloud.\n\tThe idols of Egypt
        tremble.\n\tThe hearts of the Egyptians melt with fear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will make Egyptian fight against Egyptian\u2014\n\tbrother
        against brother,\n\tneighbor against neighbor,\n\tcity against city,\n\tprovince
        against province.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Egyptians will lose heart,\n\tand I will confuse their plans.\n\tThey
        will plead with their idols for wisdom\n\tand call on spirits, mediums, and
        those who consult the spirits of the dead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will hand Egypt over\n\tto a hard, cruel master.\n\tA fierce king
        will rule them,\u201D\n\tsays the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The waters of the Nile will fail to rise and flood the fields.\n\tThe
        riverbed will be parched and dry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The canals of the Nile will dry up,\n\tand the streams of Egypt will
        stink\n\twith rotting reeds and rushes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the greenery along the riverbank\n\tand all the crops along the
        river\n\twill dry up and blow away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The fishermen will lament for lack of work.\n\tThose who cast hooks
        into the Nile will groan,\n\tand those who use nets will lose heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There will be no flax for the harvesters,\n\tno thread for the weavers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be in despair,\n\tand all the workers will be sick at heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What fools are the officials of Zoan!\n\tTheir best counsel to the
        king of Egypt is stupid and wrong.\n\tWill they still boast to Pharaoh of
        their wisdom?\n\tWill they dare brag about all their wise ancestors?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where are your wise counselors, Pharaoh?\n\tLet them tell you what
        God plans,\n\twhat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        is going to do to Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The officials of Zoan are fools,\n\tand the officials of Memphis[COMMENT[0]]
        are deluded.\n\tThe leaders of the people\n\thave led Egypt astray.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Noph.
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent a spirit of foolishness
        on them,\n\tso all their suggestions are wrong.\n\tThey cause Egypt to stagger\n\tlike
        a drunk in his vomit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is nothing Egypt can do.\n\tAll are helpless\u2014\n\tthe head
        and the tail,\n\tthe noble palm branch and the lowly reed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the Egyptians will be as weak as women. They will cower
        in fear beneath the upraised fist of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just to speak the name of Israel will terrorize them, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies has laid out his plans against them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day five of Egypt\u2019s cities will follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies. They will even begin to speak Hebrew, the language
        of Canaan. One of these cities will be Heliopolis, the City of the Sun.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: will be the City of Destruction.
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day there will be an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the heart of Egypt, and there will be a monument to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at its border. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will be a sign and a witness that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies is worshiped in the land of Egypt. When the people
        cry to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for help against those who oppress
        them, he will send them a savior who will rescue them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make himself known to the Egyptians.
        Yes, they will know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and will give their sacrifices
        and offerings to him. They will make a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and will keep it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike Egypt, and then he will
        bring healing. For the Egyptians will turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and he will listen to their pleas and heal them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day Egypt and Assyria will be connected by a highway. The
        Egyptians and Assyrians will move freely between their lands, and they will
        both worship God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day Israel will be the third, along with Egypt and Assyria,
        a blessing in the midst of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will
        say, \u201CBlessed be Egypt, my people. Blessed be Assyria, the land I have
        made. Blessed be Israel, my special possession!\u201D"
      comments: []
