    - title: 
      content: 'For the king of Assyria will take away the Egyptians and Ethiopians[COMMENT[0]]
        as prisoners. He will make them walk naked and barefoot, both young and old,
        their buttocks bared, to the shame of Egypt. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Cushites.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Philistines will be thrown into panic, for they counted
        on the power of Ethiopia and boasted of their allies in Egypt! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will say, \u2018If this can happen to Egypt, what chance do
        we have? We were counting on Egypt to protect us from the king of Assyria.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Babylon
      content: "This message came to me concerning Babylon\u2014the desert by the
        sea[COMMENT[0]]:\n\tDisaster is roaring down on you from the desert,\n\tlike
        a whirlwind sweeping in from the Negev.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: concerning the desert by the sea.
    - title: 
      content: "I see a terrifying vision:\n\tI see the betrayer betraying,\n\tthe
        destroyer destroying.\n\tGo ahead, you Elamites and Medes,\n\tattack and
        lay siege.\n\tI will make an end\n\tto all the groaning Babylon caused.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My stomach aches and burns with pain.\n\tSharp pangs of anguish are
        upon me,\n\tlike those of a woman in labor.\n\tI grow faint when I hear what
        God is planning;\n\tI am too afraid to look.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My mind reels and my heart races.\n\tI longed for evening to come,\n\tbut
        now I am terrified of the dark.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! They are preparing a great feast.\n\tThey are spreading rugs
        for people to sit on.\n\tEveryone is eating and drinking.\n\tBut quick! Grab
        your shields and prepare for battle.\n\tYou are being attacked!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Meanwhile, the Lord said to me,\n\t\u201CPut a watchman on the city
        wall.\n\tLet him shout out what he sees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He should look for chariots\n\tdrawn by pairs of horses,\n\tand for
        riders on donkeys and camels.\n\tLet the watchman be fully alert.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the watchman[COMMENT[0]] called out,\n\t\u201CDay after day
        I have stood on the watchtower, my lord.\n\tNight after night I have remained
        at my post.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Syriac version; Masoretic Text reads '
          body: a lion.
    - title: 
      content: "Now at last\u2014look!\n\tHere comes a man in a chariot\n\twith a
        pair of horses!\u201D\n\tThen the watchman said,\n\t\u201CBabylon is fallen,
        fallen!\n\tAll the idols of Babylon\n\tlie broken on the ground!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O my people, threshed and winnowed,\n\tI have told you everything
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has said,\n\teverything
        the God of Israel has told me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Edom
      content: "This message came to me concerning Edom[COMMENT[0]]:\n\tSomeone from
        Edom[COMMENT[1]] keeps calling to me,\n\t\u201CWatchman, how much longer
        until morning?\n\tWhen will the night be over?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Dumah, '
        - ft: "which means \u201Csilence\u201D or \u201Cstillness.\u201D It is a
            wordplay on the word "
          body: Edom.
      - number: '21:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Seir, '
        - ft: another name for Edom.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The watchman replies,\n\t\u201CMorning is coming, but night will
        soon return.\n\tIf you wish to ask again, then come back and ask.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Arabia
      content: "This message came to me concerning Arabia:\n\tO caravans from Dedan,\n\thide
        in the deserts of Arabia.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O people of Tema,\n\tbring water to these thirsty people,\n\tfood
        to these weary refugees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They have fled from the sword,\n\tfrom the drawn sword,\n\tfrom the
        bent bow\n\tand the terrors of battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u201CWithin a year, counting each day,[COMMENT[0]]
        all the glory of Kedar will come to an end. "
      comments:
      - number: '21:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Within a year, as a servant bound by contract would count it. '
        - ft: 'Some ancient manuscripts read '
          body: 'Within three years, '
        - ft: as in 16:14.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Only a few of its courageous archers will survive. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Jerusalem
      content: "This message came to me concerning Jerusalem\u2014the Valley of Vision[COMMENT[0]]:\n\tWhat
        is happening?\n\tWhy is everyone running to the rooftops?  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: concerning the Valley of Vision.
    - title: 
      content: "The whole city is in a terrible uproar.\n\tWhat do I see in this
        reveling city?\n\tBodies are lying everywhere,\n\tkilled not in battle but
        by famine and disease.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All your leaders have fled.\n\tThey surrendered without resistance.\n\tThe
        people tried to slip away,\n\tbut they were captured, too.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s why I said, \u201CLeave me alone to weep;\n\tdo not try
        to comfort me.\n\tLet me cry for my people\n\tas I watch them being destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, what a day of crushing defeat!\n\tWhat a day of confusion and
        terror\n\tbrought by the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\tupon the Valley of Vision!\n\tThe walls of Jerusalem have been
        broken,\n\tand cries of death echo from the mountainsides.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Elamites are the archers,\n\twith their chariots and charioteers.\n\tThe
        men of Kir hold up the shields.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Chariots fill your beautiful valleys,\n\tand charioteers storm your
        gates.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah\u2019s defenses have been stripped away.\n\tYou run to the
        armory[COMMENT[0]] for your weapons.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'to the House of the Forest; '
        - ft: see 1 Kgs 7:2-5.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'You inspect the breaks in the walls of Jerusalem.[COMMENT[0]]You
        store up water in the lower pool.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the city of David.
    - title: 
      content: "You survey the houses and tear some down\n\tfor stone to strengthen
        the walls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Between the city walls, you build a reservoir\n\tfor water from the
        old pool.\n\tBut you never ask for help from the One who did all this.\n\tYou
        never considered the One who planned this long ago.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\tcalled you to weep and mourn.\n\tHe told you to shave your heads
        in sorrow for your sins\n\tand to wear clothes of burlap to show your remorse.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But instead, you dance and play;\n\tyou slaughter cattle and kill
        sheep.\n\tYou feast on meat and drink wine.\n\tYou say, \u201CLet\u2019s
        feast and drink,\n\tfor tomorrow we die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has revealed
        this to me: \u201CTill the day you die, you will never be forgiven for this
        sin.\u201D That is the judgment of the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message for Shebna
      content: "This is what the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, said to me: \u201CConfront Shebna, the palace administrator, and
        give him this message:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho do you think you are,\n\tand what are you doing here,\n\tbuilding
        a beautiful tomb for yourself\u2014\n\ta monument high up in the rock?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is about to hurl you away, mighty
        man.\n\tHe is going to grab you,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "crumple you into a ball,\n\tand toss you away into a distant, barren
        land.\n\tThere you will die,\n\tand your glorious chariots will be broken
        and useless.\n\tYou are a disgrace to your master!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, I will drive you out of office,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        \u201CI will pull you down from your high position. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And then I will call my servant Eliakim son of Hilkiah to replace
        you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will dress him in your royal robes and will give him your title
        and your authority. And he will be a father to the people of Jerusalem and
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give him the key to the house of David\u2014the highest position
        in the royal court. When he opens doors, no one will be able to close them;
        when he closes doors, no one will be able to open them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will bring honor to his family name, for I will drive him firmly
        in place like a nail in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will give him great responsibility, and he will bring honor
        to even the lowliest members of his family.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "They will hang on him all the glory of his father\u2019s house:
            its offspring and offshoots, all its lesser vessels, from the bowls to
            all the jars."
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies also
        says: \u201CThe time will come when I will pull out the nail that seemed
        so firm. It will come out and fall to the ground. Everything it supports
        will fall with it. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Tyre
      content: "This message came to me concerning Tyre:\n\tWail, you trading ships
        of Tarshish,\n\tfor the harbor and houses of Tyre are gone!\n\tThe rumors
        you heard in Cyprus[COMMENT[0]]are all true.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Kittim; '
        - ft: also in 23:12.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Mourn in silence, you people of the coast\n\tand you merchants of
        Sidon.\n\tYour traders crossed the sea,[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads '
          body: Those who have gone over the sea have filled you.
    - title: 
      content: "sailing over deep waters.\n\tThey brought you grain from Egypt[COMMENT[0]]and
        harvests from along the Nile.\n\tYou were the marketplace of the world.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'from Shihor, '
        - ft: a branch of the Nile River.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But now you are put to shame, city of Sidon,\n\tfor Tyre, the fortress
        of the sea, says,[COMMENT[0]]\u201CNow I am childless;\n\tI have no sons
        or daughters.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'for the god of the sea says; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: for the sea, the fortress of the sea, says.
    - title: 
      content: "When Egypt hears the news about Tyre,\n\tthere will be great sorrow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Send word now to Tarshish!\n\tWail, you people who live in distant
        lands!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is this silent ruin all that is left of your once joyous city?\n\tWhat
        a long history was yours!\n\tThink of all the colonists you sent to distant
        places.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has brought this disaster on Tyre,\n\tthat great creator of kingdoms?\n\tHer
        traders were all princes,\n\ther merchants were nobles.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has done
        it\n\tto destroy your pride\n\tand bring low all earth\u2019s nobility.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come, people of Tarshish,\n\tsweep over the land like the flooding
        Nile,\n\tfor Tyre is defenseless.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew in this verse is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> held out his hand over the sea\n\tand
        shook the kingdoms of the earth.\n\tHe has spoken out against Phoenicia,[COMMENT[0]]ordering
        that her fortresses be destroyed.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Canaan.
    - title: 
      content: "He says, \u201CNever again will you rejoice,\n\tO daughter of Sidon,
        for you have been crushed.\n\tEven if you flee to Cyprus,\n\tyou will find
        no rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at the land of Babylonia[COMMENT[0]]\u2014\n\tthe people of
        that land are gone!\n\tThe Assyrians have handed Babylon over\n\tto the wild
        animals of the desert.\n\tThey have built siege ramps against its walls,\n\ttorn
        down its palaces,\n\tand turned it to a heap of rubble.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldea.
    - title: 
      content: "Wail, you ships of Tarshish,\n\tfor your harbor is destroyed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For seventy years, the length of a king\u2019s life, Tyre will be
        forgotten. But then the city will come back to life as in the song about
        the prostitute:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Take a harp and walk the streets,\n\tyou forgotten harlot.\n\tMake
        sweet melody and sing your songs\n\tso you will be remembered again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, after seventy years the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will revive
        Tyre. But she will be no different than she was before. She will again be
        a prostitute to all kingdoms around the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But in the end her profits will be given to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        Her wealth will not be hoarded but will provide good food and fine clothing
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s priests."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Destruction of the Earth
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is about to destroy the earth\n\tand
        make it a vast wasteland.\n\tHe devastates the surface of the earth\n\tand
        scatters the people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Priests and laypeople,\n\tservants and masters,\n\tmaids and mistresses,\n\tbuyers
        and sellers,\n\tlenders and borrowers,\n\tbankers and debtors\u2014none will
        be spared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth will be completely emptied and looted.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth mourns and dries up,\n\tand the land wastes away and withers.\n\tEven
        the greatest people on earth waste away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth suffers for the sins of its people,\n\tfor they have twisted
        God\u2019s instructions,\n\tviolated his laws,\n\tand broken his everlasting
        covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, a curse consumes the earth.\n\tIts people must pay the
        price for their sin.\n\tThey are destroyed by fire,\n\tand only a few are
        left alive.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The grapevines waste away,\n\tand there is no new wine.\n\tAll the
        merrymakers sigh and mourn.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The cheerful sound of tambourines is stilled;\n\tthe happy cries
        of celebration are heard no more.\n\tThe melodious chords of the harp are
        silent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gone are the joys of wine and song;\n\talcoholic drink turns bitter
        in the mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The city writhes in chaos;\n\tevery home is locked to keep out intruders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mobs gather in the streets, crying out for wine.\n\tJoy has turned
        to gloom.\n\tGladness has been banished from the land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The city is left in ruins,\n\tits gates battered down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Throughout the earth the story is the same\u2014\n\tonly a remnant
        is left,\n\tlike the stray olives left on the tree\n\tor the few grapes left
        on the vine after harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But all who are left shout and sing for joy.\n\tThose in the west
        praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In eastern lands, give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tIn
        the lands beyond the sea, praise the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We hear songs of praise from the ends of the earth,\n\tsongs that
        give glory to the Righteous One!\n\tBut my heart is heavy with grief.\n\tWeep
        for me, for I wither away.\n\tDeceit still prevails,\n\tand treachery is
        everywhere.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Terror and traps and snares will be your lot,\n\tyou people of the
        earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who flee in terror will fall into a trap,\n\tand those who
        escape the trap will be caught in a snare.\n\tDestruction falls like rain
        from the heavens;\n\tthe foundations of the earth shake.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth has broken up.\n\tIt has utterly collapsed;\n\tit is violently
        shaken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth staggers like a drunk.\n\tIt trembles like a tent in a
        storm.\n\tIt falls and will not rise again,\n\tfor the guilt of its rebellion
        is very heavy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will punish the gods
        in the heavens\n\tand the proud rulers of the nations on earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be rounded up and put in prison.\n\tThey will be shut up
        in prison\n\tand will finally be punished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the glory of the moon will wane,\n\tand the brightness of the
        sun will fade,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        will rule on Mount Zion.\n\tHe will rule in great glory in Jerusalem,\n\tin
        the sight of all the leaders of his people."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Praise for Judgment and Salvation
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, I will honor and praise your name,\n\tfor
        you are my God.\n\tYou do such wonderful things!\n\tYou planned them long
        ago,\n\tand now you have accomplished them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You turn mighty cities into heaps of ruins.\n\tCities with strong
        walls are turned to rubble.\n\tBeautiful palaces in distant lands disappear\n\tand
        will never be rebuilt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, strong nations will declare your glory;\n\truthless nations
        will fear you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you are a tower of refuge to the poor, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\ta
        tower of refuge to the needy in distress.\n\tYou are a refuge from the storm\n\tand
        a shelter from the heat.\n\tFor the oppressive acts of ruthless people\n\tare
        like a storm beating against a wall,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "or like the relentless heat of the desert.\n\tBut you silence the
        roar of foreign nations.\n\tAs the shade of a cloud cools relentless heat,\n\tso
        the boastful songs of ruthless people are stilled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies\n\twill spread a wonderful feast\n\tfor all the people of the world.\n\tIt
        will be a delicious banquet\n\twith clear, well-aged wine and choice meat.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'On this mountain; '
        - ft: also in 25:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "There he will remove the cloud of gloom,\n\tthe shadow of death that
        hangs over the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will swallow up death forever!\n\tThe Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will wipe away all tears.\n\tHe will remove forever all insults and mockery\n\tagainst
        his land and people.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the people will proclaim,\n\t\u201CThis is our God!\n\tWe
        trusted in him, and he saved us!\n\tThis is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        in whom we trusted.\n\tLet us rejoice in the salvation he brings!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s hand of blessing will
        rest on Jerusalem.\n\tBut Moab will be crushed.\n\tIt will be like straw
        trampled down and left to rot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God will push down Moab\u2019s people\n\tas a swimmer pushes down
        water with his hands.\n\tHe will end their pride\n\tand all their evil works.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The high walls of Moab will be demolished.\n\tThey will be brought
        down to the ground,\n\tdown into the dust."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Lord
      content: "In that day, everyone in the land of Judah will sing this song:\n\tOur
        city is strong!\n\tWe are surrounded by the walls of God\u2019s salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Open the gates to all who are righteous;\n\tallow the faithful to
        enter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will keep in perfect peace\n\tall who trust in you,\n\tall whose
        thoughts are fixed on you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> always,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord
        God</smallcaps> is the eternal Rock.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He humbles the proud\n\tand brings down the arrogant city.\n\tHe
        brings it down to the dust.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The poor and oppressed trample it underfoot,\n\tand the needy walk
        all over it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But for those who are righteous,\n\tthe way is not steep and rough.\n\tYou
        are a God who does what is right,\n\tand you smooth out the path ahead of
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, we show our trust in you by obeying
        your laws;\n\tour heart\u2019s desire is to glorify your name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the night I search for you;\n\tin the morning[COMMENT[0]] I earnestly
        seek you.\n\tFor only when you come to judge the earth\n\twill people learn
        what is right.  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: within me.
    - title: 
      content: "Your kindness to the wicked\n\tdoes not make them do good.\n\tAlthough
        others do right, the wicked keep doing wrong\n\tand take no notice of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, they pay no attention to your
        upraised fist.\n\tShow them your eagerness to defend your people.\n\tThen
        they will be ashamed.\n\tLet your fire consume your enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you will grant us peace;\n\tall
        we have accomplished is really from you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, others have ruled us,\n\tbut
        you alone are the one we worship.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those we served before are dead and gone.\n\tTheir departed spirits
        will never return!\n\tYou attacked them and destroyed them,\n\tand they are
        long forgotten.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you have made our nation great;\n\tyes,
        you have made us great.\n\tYou have extended our borders,\n\tand we give
        you the glory!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, in distress we searched for you.\n\tWe
        prayed beneath the burden of your discipline.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just as a pregnant woman\n\twrithes and cries out in pain as she
        gives birth,\n\tso were we in your presence, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We, too, writhe in agony,\n\tbut nothing comes of our suffering.\n\tWe
        have not given salvation to the earth,\n\tnor brought life into the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who die in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will live;\n\ttheir
        bodies will rise again!\n\tThose who sleep in the earth\n\twill rise up and
        sing for joy!\n\tFor your life-giving light will fall like dew\n\ton your
        people in the place of the dead!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Restoration for Israel
      content: "Go home, my people,\n\tand lock your doors!\n\tHide yourselves for
        a little while\n\tuntil the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger
        has passed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming from heaven\n\tto
        punish the people of the earth for their sins.\n\tThe earth will no longer
        hide those who have been killed.\n\tThey will be brought out for all to see."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will take his terrible,
        swift sword and punish Leviathan,[COMMENT[0]] the swiftly moving serpent,
        the coiling, writhing serpent. He will kill the dragon of the sea.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
            creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\n\tsing about the fruitful vineyard.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, will watch over it,\n\twatering
        it carefully.\n\tDay and night I will watch so no one can harm it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My anger will be gone.\n\tIf I find briers and thorns growing,\n\tI
        will attack them;\n\tI will burn them up\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "unless they turn to me for help.\n\tLet them make peace with me;\n\tyes,
        let them make peace with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The time is coming when Jacob\u2019s descendants will take root.\n\tIsrael
        will bud and blossom\n\tand fill the whole earth with fruit!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> struck Israel\n\tas he struck
        her enemies?\n\tHas he punished her\n\tas he punished them?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, but he exiled Israel to call her to account.\n\tShe was exiled
        from her land\n\tas though blown away in a storm from the east.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did this to purge Israel\u2019s[COMMENT[0]]
        wickedness,\n\tto take away all her sin.\n\tAs a result, all the pagan altars
        will be crushed to dust.\n\tNo Asherah pole or pagan shrine will be left
        standing.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "Jacob\u2019s. "
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The fortified towns will be silent and empty,\n\tthe houses abandoned,
        the streets overgrown with weeds.\n\tCalves will graze there,\n\tchewing
        on twigs and branches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people are like the dead branches of a tree,\n\tbroken off and
        used for kindling beneath the cooking pots.\n\tIsrael is a foolish and stupid
        nation,\n\tfor its people have turned away from God.\n\tTherefore, the one
        who made them\n\twill show them no pity or mercy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet the time will come when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        gather them together like handpicked grain. One by one he will gather them\u2014from
        the Euphrates River[COMMENT[0]] in the east to the Brook of Egypt in the
        west. "
      comments:
      - number: '27:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the river.
    - title: 
      content: In that day the great trumpet will sound. Many who were dying in exile
        in Assyria and Egypt will return to Jerusalem to worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        on his holy mountain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Samaria
      content: "What sorrow awaits the proud city of Samaria\u2014\n\tthe glorious
        crown of the drunks of Israel.[COMMENT[0]]It sits at the head of a fertile
        valley,\n\tbut its glorious beauty will fade like a flower.\n\tIt is the
        pride of a people\n\tbrought down by wine.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'What sorrow awaits the crowning glory of the drunks of Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to Samaria, capital of the northern kingdom of Israel.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "For the Lord will send a mighty army against it.\n\tLike a mighty
        hailstorm and a torrential rain,\n\tthey will burst upon it like a surging
        flood\n\tand smash it to the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The proud city of Samaria\u2014\n\tthe glorious crown of the drunks
        of Israel[COMMENT[0]]\u2014\n\twill be trampled beneath its enemies\u2019
        feet.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'The crowning glory of the drunks of Ephraim; '
        - ft: see note on 28:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "It sits at the head of a fertile valley,\n\tbut its glorious beauty
        will fade like a flower.\n\tWhoever sees it will snatch it up,\n\tas an early
        fig is quickly picked and eaten.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then at last the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\twill
        himself be Israel\u2019s glorious crown.\n\tHe will be the pride and joy\n\tof
        the remnant of his people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will give a longing for justice\n\tto their judges.\n\tHe will
        give great courage\n\tto their warriors who stand at the gates.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now, however, Israel is led by drunks\n\twho reel with wine and stagger
        with alcohol.\n\tThe priests and prophets stagger with alcohol\n\tand lose
        themselves in wine.\n\tThey reel when they see visions\n\tand stagger as
        they render decisions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their tables are covered with vomit;\n\tfilth is everywhere.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho does the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> think we are?\u201D
        they ask.\n\t\u201CWhy does he speak to us like this?\n\tAre we little children,\n\tjust
        recently weaned?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He tells us everything over and over\u2014\n\tone line at a time,\n\tone
        line at a time,\n\ta little here,\n\tand a little there!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now God will have to speak to his people\n\tthrough foreign oppressors
        who speak a strange language!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has told his people,\n\t\u201CHere is a place of rest;\n\tlet
        the weary rest here.\n\tThis is a place of quiet rest.\u201D\n\tBut they
        would not listen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will spell out his message for
        them again,\n\tone line at a time,\n\tone line at a time,\n\ta little here,\n\tand
        a little there,\n\tso that they will stumble and fall.\n\tThey will be injured,
        trapped, and captured.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tyou
        scoffing rulers in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You boast, \u201CWe have struck a bargain to cheat death\n\tand have
        made a deal to dodge the grave.[COMMENT[0]]The coming destruction can never
        touch us,\n\tfor we have built a strong refuge made of lies and deception.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Sheol; '
        - ft: also in 28:18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201CLook! I am placing a foundation stone in Jerusalem,[COMMENT[0]]a
        firm and tested stone.\n\tIt is a precious cornerstone that is safe to build
        on.\n\tWhoever believes need never be shaken.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:16a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Zion.
      - number: '28:16b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Look! I am placing a stone in the foundation of Jerusalem '
        - ft: '[literally '
          body: Zion
        - ft: '], '
          body: '/ a precious cornerstone for its foundation, chosen for great honor.
            / Anyone who trusts in him will never be disgraced. '
        - ft: Compare Rom 9:33; 1 Pet 2:6.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will test you with the measuring line of justice\n\tand the plumb
        line of righteousness.\n\tSince your refuge is made of lies,\n\ta hailstorm
        will knock it down.\n\tSince it is made of deception,\n\ta flood will sweep
        it away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will cancel the bargain you made to cheat death,\n\tand I will
        overturn your deal to dodge the grave.\n\tWhen the terrible enemy sweeps
        through,\n\tyou will be trampled into the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again and again that flood will come,\n\tmorning after morning,\n\tday
        and night,\n\tuntil you are carried away.\u201D\n\tThis message will bring
        terror to your people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The bed you have made is too short to lie on.\n\tThe blankets are
        too narrow to cover you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will come as he did against the Philistines
        at Mount Perazim\n\tand against the Amorites at Gibeon.\n\tHe will come to
        do a strange thing;\n\the will come to do an unusual deed:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\n\thas
        plainly said that he is determined to crush the whole land.\n\tSo scoff no
        more,\n\tor your punishment will be even greater.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to me;\n\tlisten, and pay close attention.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does a farmer always plow and never sow?\n\tIs he forever cultivating
        the soil and never planting?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does he not finally plant his seeds\u2014\n\tblack cumin, cumin,
        wheat, barley, and emmer wheat\u2014\n\teach in its proper way,\n\tand each
        in its proper place?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The farmer knows just what to do,\n\tfor God has given him understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A heavy sledge is never used to thresh black cumin;\n\trather, it
        is beaten with a light stick.\n\tA threshing wheel is never rolled on cumin;\n\tinstead,
        it is beaten lightly with a flail.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Grain for bread is easily crushed,\n\tso he doesn\u2019t keep on
        pounding it.\n\tHe threshes it under the wheels of a cart,\n\tbut he doesn\u2019t
        pulverize it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is a wonderful
        teacher,\n\tand he gives the farmer great wisdom."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Jerusalem
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits Ariel,[COMMENT[0]] the City of David.\n\tYear
        after year you celebrate your feasts.  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Ariel '
        - ft: "sounds like a Hebrew term that means \u201Chearth\u201D or \u201Caltar.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Yet I will bring disaster upon you,\n\tand there will be much weeping
        and sorrow.\n\tFor Jerusalem will become what her name Ariel means\u2014\n\tan
        altar covered with blood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be your enemy,\n\tsurrounding Jerusalem and attacking its
        walls.\n\tI will build siege towers\n\tand destroy it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then deep from the earth you will speak;\n\tfrom low in the dust
        your words will come.\n\tYour voice will whisper from the ground\n\tlike
        a ghost conjured up from the grave.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suddenly, your ruthless enemies will be crushed\n\tlike
        the finest of dust.\n\tYour many attackers will be driven away\n\tlike chaff
        before the wind.\n\tSuddenly, in an instant,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, will
        act for you\n\twith thunder and earthquake and great noise,\n\twith whirlwind
        and storm and consuming fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the nations fighting against Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]will vanish
        like a dream!\n\tThose who are attacking her walls\n\twill vanish like a
        vision in the night.  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Ariel.
    - title: 
      content: "A hungry person dreams of eating\n\tbut wakes up still hungry.\n\tA
        thirsty person dreams of drinking\n\tbut is still faint from thirst when
        morning comes.\n\tSo it will be with your enemies,\n\twith those who attack
        Mount Zion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you amazed and incredulous?\n\tDon\u2019t you believe it?\n\tThen
        go ahead and be blind.\n\tYou are stupid, but not from wine!\n\tYou stagger,
        but not from liquor!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has poured out on you a spirit
        of deep sleep.\n\tHe has closed the eyes of your prophets and visionaries.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the future events in this vision are like a sealed book to them.
        When you give it to those who can read, they will say, \u201CWe can\u2019t
        read it because it is sealed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you give it to those who cannot read, they will say, \u201CWe
        don\u2019t know how to read.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And so the Lord says,\n\t\u201CThese people say they are mine.\n\tThey
        honor me with their lips,\n\tbut their hearts are far from me.\n\tAnd their
        worship of me\n\tis nothing but man-made rules learned by rote.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Their worship is a farce, / for they teach man-made ideas as commands
            from God. '
        - ft: Compare Mark 7:7.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Because of this, I will once again astound these hypocrites\n\twith
        amazing wonders.\n\tThe wisdom of the wise will pass away,\n\tand the intelligence
        of the intelligent will disappear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow awaits those who try to hide their plans from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\twho
        do their evil deeds in the dark!\n\t\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        can\u2019t see us,\u201D they say.\n\t\u201CHe doesn\u2019t know what\u2019s
        going on!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How foolish can you be?\n\tHe is the Potter, and he is certainly
        greater than you, the clay!\n\tShould the created thing say of the one who
        made it,\n\t\u201CHe didn\u2019t make me\u201D?\n\tDoes a jar ever say,\n\t\u201CThe
        potter who made me is stupid\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon\u2014and it will not be very long\u2014\n\tthe forests of Lebanon
        will become a fertile field,\n\tand the fertile field will yield bountiful
        crops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the deaf will hear words read from a book,\n\tand the
        blind will see through the gloom and darkness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The humble will be filled with fresh joy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThe
        poor will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The scoffer will be gone,\n\tthe arrogant will disappear,\n\tand
        those who plot evil will be killed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who convict the innocent\n\tby their false testimony will disappear.\n\tA
        similar fate awaits those who use trickery to pervert justice\n\tand who
        tell lies to destroy the innocent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, who redeemed Abraham,
        says to the people of Israel,[COMMENT[0]]\u201CMy people will no longer be
        ashamed\n\tor turn pale with fear.  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "For when they see their many children\n\tand all the blessings I
        have given them,\n\tthey will recognize the holiness of the Holy One of Jacob.\n\tThey
        will stand in awe of the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the wayward will gain understanding,\n\tand complainers will
        accept instruction."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Worthless Treaty with Egypt"
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits my rebellious children,\u201D\n\tsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CYou make plans that are contrary
        to mine.\n\tYou make alliances not directed by my Spirit,\n\tthus piling
        up your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For without consulting me,\n\tyou have gone down to Egypt for help.\n\tYou
        have put your trust in Pharaoh\u2019s protection.\n\tYou have tried to hide
        in his shade.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But by trusting Pharaoh, you will be humiliated,\n\tand by depending
        on him, you will be disgraced.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For though his power extends to Zoan\n\tand his officials have arrived
        in Hanes,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "all who trust in him will be ashamed.\n\tHe will not help you.\n\tInstead,
        he will disgrace you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This message came to me concerning the animals in the Negev:\n\tThe
        caravan moves slowly\n\tacross the terrible desert to Egypt\u2014\n\tdonkeys
        weighed down with riches\n\tand camels loaded with treasure\u2014\n\tall
        to pay for Egypt\u2019s protection.\n\tThey travel through the wilderness,\n\ta
        place of lionesses and lions,\n\ta place where vipers and poisonous snakes
        live.\n\tAll this, and Egypt will give you nothing in return.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Egypt\u2019s promises are worthless!\n\tTherefore, I call her Rahab\u2014\n\tthe
        Harmless Dragon.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Rahab who sits still. '
        - ft: Rahab is the name of a mythical sea monster that represents chaos in
            ancient literature. The name is used here as a poetic name for Egypt.
          body: 
    - title: A Warning for Rebellious Judah
      content: "Now go and write down these words.\n\tWrite them in a book.\n\tThey
        will stand until the end of time\n\tas a witness  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that these people are stubborn rebels\n\twho refuse to pay attention
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They tell the seers,\n\t\u201CStop seeing visions!\u201D\n\tThey
        tell the prophets,\n\t\u201CDon\u2019t tell us what is right.\n\tTell us
        nice things.\n\tTell us lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Forget all this gloom.\n\tGet off your narrow path.\n\tStop telling
        us about your\n\t\u2018Holy One of Israel.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is the reply of the Holy One of Israel:\n\t\u201CBecause you
        despise what I tell you\n\tand trust instead in oppression and lies,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "calamity will come upon you suddenly\u2014\n\tlike a bulging wall
        that bursts and falls.\n\tIn an instant it will collapse\n\tand come crashing
        down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be smashed like a piece of pottery\u2014\n\tshattered so
        completely that\n\tthere won\u2019t be a piece big enough\n\tto carry coals
        from a fireplace\n\tor a little water from the well.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe
        Holy One of Israel, says:\n\t\u201COnly in returning to me\n\tand resting
        in me will you be saved.\n\tIn quietness and confidence is your strength.\n\tBut
        you would have none of it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018No, we will get our help from Egypt.\n\tThey will
        give us swift horses for riding into battle.\u2019\n\tBut the only swiftness
        you are going to see\n\tis the swiftness of your enemies chasing you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One of them will chase a thousand of you.\n\tFive of them will make
        all of you flee.\n\tYou will be left like a lonely flagpole on a hill\n\tor
        a tattered banner on a distant mountaintop.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s People"
      content: "So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> must wait for you to come to him\n\tso
        he can show you his love and compassion.\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is a faithful God.\n\tBlessed are those who wait for his help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O people of Zion, who live in Jerusalem,\n\tyou will weep no more.\n\tHe
        will be gracious if you ask for help.\n\tHe will surely respond to the sound
        of your cries.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though the Lord gave you adversity for food\n\tand suffering for
        drink,\n\the will still be with you to teach you.\n\tYou will see your teacher
        with your own eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your own ears will hear him.\n\tRight behind you a voice will say,\n\t\u201CThis
        is the way you should go,\u201D\n\twhether to the right or to the left.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will destroy all your silver idols\n\tand your precious
        gold images.\n\tYou will throw them out like filthy rags,\n\tsaying to them,
        \u201CGood riddance!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bless you with rain at
        planting time. There will be wonderful harvests and plenty of pastureland
        for your livestock. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The oxen and donkeys that till the ground will eat good grain, its
        chaff blown away by the wind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day, when your enemies are slaughtered and the towers fall,
        there will be streams of water flowing down every mountain and hill. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The moon will be as bright as the sun, and the sun will be seven
        times brighter\u2014like the light of seven days in one! So it will be when
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> begins to heal his people and cure the wounds
        he gave them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming from far away,\n\tburning
        with anger,\n\tsurrounded by thick, rising smoke.\n\tHis lips are filled
        with fury;\n\this words consume like fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His hot breath pours out like a flood\n\tup to the neck of his enemies.\n\tHe
        will sift out the proud nations for destruction.\n\tHe will bridle them and
        lead them away to ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people of God will sing a song of joy,\n\tlike the songs
        at the holy festivals.\n\tYou will be filled with joy,\n\tas when a flutist
        leads a group of pilgrims\n\tto Jerusalem, the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2014\n\tto
        the Rock of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make his majestic voice
        heard.\n\tHe will display the strength of his mighty arm.\n\tIt will descend
        with devouring flames,\n\twith cloudbursts, thunderstorms, and huge hailstones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s command, the Assyrians
        will be shattered.\n\tHe will strike them down with his royal scepter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> strikes them with his rod
        of punishment,[COMMENT[0]]his people will celebrate with tambourines and
        harps.\n\tLifting his mighty arm, he will fight the Assyrians.  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version; Masoretic Text reads '
          body: with the founded rod.
    - title: 
      content: "Topheth\u2014the place of burning\u2014\n\thas long been ready for
        the Assyrian king;\n\tthe pyre is piled high with wood.\n\tThe breath of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, like fire from a volcano,\n\twill set
        it ablaze."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Futility of Relying on Egypt
      content: "What sorrow awaits those who look to Egypt for help,\n\ttrusting
        their horses, chariots, and charioteers\n\tand depending on the strength
        of human armies\n\tinstead of looking to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthe
        Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In his wisdom, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will send great disaster;\n\the
        will not change his mind.\n\tHe will rise against the wicked\n\tand against
        their helpers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For these Egyptians are mere humans, not God!\n\tTheir horses are
        puny flesh, not mighty spirits!\n\tWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raises
        his fist against them,\n\tthose who help will stumble,\n\tand those being
        helped will fall.\n\tThey will all fall down and die together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told me:\n\t\u201CWhen
        a strong young lion\n\tstands growling over a sheep it has killed,\n\tit
        is not frightened by the shouts and noise\n\tof a whole crowd of shepherds.\n\tIn
        the same way, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\twill
        come down and fight on Mount Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will hover
        over Jerusalem\n\tand protect it like a bird protecting its nest.\n\tHe will
        defend and save the city;\n\the will pass over it and rescue it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though you are such wicked rebels, my people, come and return to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know the glorious day will come when each of you will throw away
        the gold idols and silver images your sinful hands have made.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Assyrians will be destroyed,\n\tbut not by the swords of
        men.\n\tThe sword of God will strike them,\n\tand they will panic and flee.\n\tThe
        strong young Assyrians\n\twill be taken away as captives.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the strongest will quake with terror,\n\tand princes will flee
        when they see your battle flags,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        whose fire burns in Zion,\n\twhose flame blazes from Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Ultimate Deliverance"
      content: "Look, a righteous king is coming!\n\tAnd honest princes will rule
        under him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each one will be like a shelter from the wind\n\tand a refuge from
        the storm,\n\tlike streams of water in the desert\n\tand the shadow of a
        great rock in a parched land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then everyone who has eyes will be able to see the truth,\n\tand
        everyone who has ears will be able to hear it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the hotheads will be full of sense and understanding.\n\tThose
        who stammer will speak out plainly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day ungodly fools will not be heroes.\n\tScoundrels will
        not be respected.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For fools speak foolishness\n\tand make evil plans.\n\tThey practice
        ungodliness\n\tand spread false teachings about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThey
        deprive the hungry of food\n\tand give no water to the thirsty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The smooth tricks of scoundrels are evil.\n\tThey plot crooked schemes.\n\tThey
        lie to convict the poor,\n\teven when the cause of the poor is just.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But generous people plan to do what is generous,\n\tand they stand
