      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, rescue us from his power;
        then all the kingdoms of the earth will know that you alone, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        are God.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls (see also 2 Kgs 19:19); Masoretic Text reads '
          body: 'you alone are the '
    - title: "Isaiah Predicts Judah\u2019s Deliverance"
      content: "Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent this message to Hezekiah: \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the God of Israel, says: Because
        you prayed about King Sennacherib of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken this word against him:\n\t\u201CThe
        virgin daughter of Zion\n\tdespises you and laughs at you.\n\tThe daughter
        of Jerusalem\n\tshakes her head in derision as you flee.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhom have you been defying and ridiculing?\n\tAgainst whom
        did you raise your voice?\n\tAt whom did you look with such haughty eyes?\n\tIt
        was the Holy One of Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By your messengers you have defied the Lord.\n\tYou have said, \u2018With
        my many chariots\n\tI have conquered the highest mountains\u2014\n\tyes,
        the remotest peaks of Lebanon.\n\tI have cut down its tallest cedars\n\tand
        its finest cypress trees.\n\tI have reached its farthest heights\n\tand explored
        its deepest forests.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have dug wells in many foreign lands[COMMENT[0]]and refreshed myself
        with their water.\n\tWith the sole of my foot,\n\tI stopped up all the rivers
        of Egypt!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls (see also 2 Kgs 19:24); Masoretic Text lacks '
          body: in many foreign lands.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut have you not heard?\n\tI decided this long ago.\n\tLong
        ago I planned it,\n\tand now I am making it happen.\n\tI planned for you
        to crush fortified cities\n\tinto heaps of rubble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why their people have so little power\n\tand are so frightened
        and confused.\n\tThey are as weak as grass,\n\tas easily trampled as tender
        green shoots.\n\tThey are like grass sprouting on a housetop,\n\tscorched[COMMENT[0]]
        before it can grow lush and tall.  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls and some Greek manuscripts (see also 2 Kgs
            19:26); most Hebrew manuscripts read '
          body: like a terraced field.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I know you well\u2014\n\twhere you stay\n\tand when you
        come and go.\n\tI know the way you have raged against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And because of your raging against me\n\tand your arrogance, which
        I have heard for myself,\n\tI will put my hook in your nose\n\tand my bit
        in your mouth.\n\tI will make you return\n\tby the same road on which you
        came.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHere is the proof that what I
        say is true:\n\t\u201CThis year you will eat only what grows up by itself,\n\tand
        next year you will eat what springs up from that.\n\tBut in the third year
        you will plant crops and harvest them;\n\tyou will tend vineyards and eat
        their fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you who are left in Judah,\n\twho have escaped the ravages of
        the siege,\n\twill put roots down in your own soil\n\tand grow up and flourish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For a remnant of my people will spread out from Jerusalem,\n\ta group
        of survivors from Mount Zion.\n\tThe passionate commitment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies\n\twill make this happen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about
        the king of Assyria:\n\t\u201C\u2018His armies will not enter Jerusalem.\n\tThey
        will not even shoot an arrow at it.\n\tThey will not march outside its gates
        with their shields\n\tnor build banks of earth against its walls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The king will return to his own country\n\tby the same road on which
        he came.\n\tHe will not enter this city,\u2019\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018For my own honor and for the sake of my servant David,\n\tI
        will defend this city and protect it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That night the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went out
        to the Assyrian camp and killed 185,000 Assyrian soldiers. When the surviving
        Assyrians[COMMENT[0]] woke up the next morning, they found corpses everywhere. '
      comments:
      - number: '37:36 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: When they.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then King Sennacherib of Assyria broke camp and returned to his own
        land. He went home to his capital of Nineveh and stayed there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: One day while he was worshiping in the temple of his god Nisroch,
        his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer killed him with their swords. They then
        escaped to the land of Ararat, and another son, Esarhaddon, became the next
        king of Assyria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Sickness and Recovery"
      content: "About that time Hezekiah became deathly ill, and the prophet Isaiah
        son of Amoz went to visit him. He gave the king this message: \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Set your affairs in order,
        for you are going to die. You will not recover from this illness.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Hezekiah heard this, he turned his face to the wall and prayed
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRemember, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, how I have always
        been faithful to you and have served you single-mindedly, always doing what
        pleases you.\u201D Then he broke down and wept bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then this message came to Isaiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo back to Hezekiah and tell him, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of your ancestor David, says: I have heard your prayer and seen your
        tears. I will add fifteen years to your life, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and I will rescue you and this city from the king of Assyria. Yes,
        I will defend this city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018And this is the sign from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to prove that he will do as he promised: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will cause the sun\u2019s shadow to move ten steps backward on
        the sundial[COMMENT[0]] of Ahaz!\u2019\u201D So the shadow on the sundial
        moved backward ten steps.  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the steps.
    - title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Poem of Praise"
      content: 'When King Hezekiah was well again, he wrote this poem:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u201CIn the prime of my life,\n\tmust I now enter the place
        of the dead?[COMMENT[0]]Am I to be robbed of the rest of my years?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: enter the gates of Sheol?
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u201CNever again will I see the <smallcaps>Lord God</smallcaps>\n\twhile
        still in the land of the living.\n\tNever again will I see my friends\n\tor
        be with those who live in this world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My life has been blown away\n\tlike a shepherd\u2019s tent in a storm.\n\tIt
        has been cut short,\n\tas when a weaver cuts cloth from a loom.\n\tSuddenly,
        my life was over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I waited patiently all night,\n\tbut I was torn apart as though by
        lions.\n\tSuddenly, my life was over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Delirious, I chattered like a swallow or a crane,\n\tand then I moaned
        like a mourning dove.\n\tMy eyes grew tired of looking to heaven for help.\n\tI
        am in trouble, Lord. Help me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But what could I say?\n\tFor he himself sent this sickness.\n\tNow
        I will walk humbly throughout my years\n\tbecause of this anguish I have
        felt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lord, your discipline is good,\n\tfor it leads to life and health.\n\tYou
        restore my health\n\tand allow me to live!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, this anguish was good for me,\n\tfor you have rescued me from
        death\n\tand forgiven all my sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the dead[COMMENT[0]] cannot praise you;\n\tthey cannot raise
        their voices in praise.\n\tThose who go down to the grave\n\tcan no longer
        hope in your faithfulness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "Only the living can praise you as I do today.\n\tEach generation
        tells of your faithfulness to the next.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Think of it\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is ready to heal
        me!\n\tI will sing his praises with instruments\n\tevery day of my life\n\tin
        the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isaiah had said to Hezekiah\u2019s servants, \u201CMake an ointment
        from figs and spread it over the boil, and Hezekiah will recover.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Hezekiah had asked, \u201CWhat sign will prove that I will go
        to the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Envoys from Babylon
      content: 'Soon after this, Merodach-baladan son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent Hezekiah his best wishes and a gift. He had heard that Hezekiah had
        been very sick and that he had recovered. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hezekiah was delighted with the Babylonian envoys and showed them
        everything in his treasure-houses\u2014the silver, the gold, the spices,
        and the aromatic oils. He also took them to see his armory and showed them
        everything in his royal treasuries! There was nothing in his palace or kingdom
        that Hezekiah did not show them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah and asked him, \u201CWhat
        did those men want? Where were they from?\u201D\n\tHezekiah replied, \u201CThey
        came from the distant land of Babylon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat did they see in your palace?\u201D asked Isaiah.\n\t\u201CThey
        saw everything,\u201D Hezekiah replied. \u201CI showed them everything I
        own\u2014all my royal treasuries.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CListen to this message from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018The time is coming when everything in your palace\u2014all
        the treasures stored up by your ancestors until now\u2014will be carried
        off to Babylon. Nothing will be left,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Some of your very own sons will be taken away into exile. They
        will become eunuchs who will serve in the palace of Babylon\u2019s king.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThis message you have given me
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good.\u201D For the king was thinking,
        \u201CAt least there will be peace and security during my lifetime.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      content: "\u201CComfort, comfort my people,\u201D\n\tsays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSpeak tenderly to Jerusalem.\n\tTell her that her sad days
        are gone\n\tand her sins are pardoned.\n\tYes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has punished her twice over\n\tfor all her sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen! It\u2019s the voice of someone shouting,\n\t\u201CClear the
        way through the wilderness\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tMake
        a straight highway through the wasteland\n\tfor our God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fill in the valleys,\n\tand level the mountains and hills.\n\tStraighten
        the curves,\n\tand smooth out the rough places.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be revealed,\n\tand
        all people will see it together.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken!\u201D[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
