    - title: 
      content: "Yes, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming in power.\n\tHe
        will rule with a powerful arm.\n\tSee, he brings his reward with him as he
        comes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will feed his flock like a shepherd.\n\tHe will carry the lambs
        in his arms,\n\tholding them close to his heart.\n\tHe will gently lead the
        mother sheep with their young.  "
      comments: []
    - title: ' Has No Equal'
      content: "Who else has held the oceans in his hand?\n\tWho has measured off
        the heavens with his fingers?\n\tWho else knows the weight of the earth\n\tor
        has weighed the mountains and hills on a scale?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is able to advise the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?[COMMENT[0]]Who
        knows enough to give him advice or teach him?  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Who can know the '
        - ft: Compare Rom 11:34; 1 Cor 2:16.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> ever needed anyone\u2019s advice?\n\tDoes
        he need instruction about what is good?\n\tDid someone teach him what is
        right\n\tor show him the path of justice?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, for all the nations of the world\n\tare but a drop in the bucket.\n\tThey
        are nothing more\n\tthan dust on the scales.\n\tHe picks up the whole earth\n\tas
        though it were a grain of sand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the wood in Lebanon\u2019s forests\n\tand all Lebanon\u2019s
        animals would not be enough\n\tto make a burnt offering worthy of our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations of the world are worth nothing to him.\n\tIn his eyes
        they count for less than nothing\u2014\n\tmere emptiness and froth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To whom can you compare God?\n\tWhat image can you find to resemble
        him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can he be compared to an idol formed in a mold,\n\toverlaid with
        gold, and decorated with silver chains?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Or if people are too poor for that,\n\tthey might at least choose
        wood that won\u2019t decay\n\tand a skilled craftsman\n\tto carve an image
        that won\u2019t fall down!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Haven\u2019t you heard? Don\u2019t you understand?\n\tAre you deaf
        to the words of God\u2014\n\tthe words he gave before the world began?\n\tAre
        you so ignorant?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God sits above the circle of the earth.\n\tThe people below seem
        like grasshoppers to him!\n\tHe spreads out the heavens like a curtain\n\tand
        makes his tent from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He judges the great people of the world\n\tand brings them all to
        nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They hardly get started, barely taking root,\n\twhen he blows on
        them and they wither.\n\tThe wind carries them off like chaff.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTo whom will you compare me?\n\tWho is my equal?\u201D asks
        the Holy One.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look up into the heavens.\n\tWho created all the stars?\n\tHe brings
        them out like an army, one after another,\n\tcalling each by its name.\n\tBecause
        of his great power and incomparable strength,\n\tnot a single one is missing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Jacob, how can you say the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not
        see your troubles?\n\tO Israel, how can you say God ignores your rights?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have you never heard?\n\tHave you never understood?\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is the everlasting God,\n\tthe Creator of all the earth.\n\tHe never grows
        weak or weary.\n\tNo one can measure the depths of his understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He gives power to the weak\n\tand strength to the powerless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even youths will become weak and tired,\n\tand young men will fall
        in exhaustion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will find
        new strength.\n\tThey will soar high on wings like eagles.\n\tThey will run
        and not grow weary.\n\tThey will walk and not faint."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Help for Israel"
      content: "\u201CListen in silence before me, you lands beyond the sea.\n\tBring
        your strongest arguments.\n\tCome now and speak.\n\tThe court is ready for
        your case.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho has stirred up this king from the east,\n\trightly calling
        him to God\u2019s service?\n\tWho gives this man victory over many nations\n\tand
        permits him to trample their kings underfoot?\n\tWith his sword, he reduces
        armies to dust.\n\tWith his bow, he scatters them like chaff before the wind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He chases them away and goes on safely,\n\tthough he is walking over
        unfamiliar ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has done such mighty deeds,\n\tsummoning each new generation
        from the beginning of time?\n\tIt is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the First and the Last.\n\tI alone am he.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lands beyond the sea watch in fear.\n\tRemote lands tremble and
        mobilize for war.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The idol makers encourage one another,\n\tsaying to each other, \u201CBe
        strong!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The carver encourages the goldsmith,\n\tand the molder helps at the
        anvil.\n\t\u201CGood,\u201D they say. \u201CIt\u2019s coming along fine.\u201D\n\tCarefully
        they join the parts together,\n\tthen fasten the thing in place so it won\u2019t
        fall over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as for you, Israel my servant,\n\tJacob my chosen one,\n\tdescended
        from Abraham my friend,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have called you back from the ends of the earth,\n\tsaying, \u2018You
        are my servant.\u2019\n\tFor I have chosen you\n\tand will not throw you
        away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, for I am with you.\n\tDon\u2019t be discouraged,
        for I am your God.\n\tI will strengthen you and help you.\n\tI will hold
        you up with my victorious right hand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSee, all your angry enemies lie there,\n\tconfused and humiliated.\n\tAnyone
        who opposes you will die\n\tand come to nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will look in vain\n\tfor those who tried to conquer you.\n\tThose
        who attack you\n\twill come to nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I hold you by your right hand\u2014\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.\n\tAnd I say to you,\n\t\u2018Don\u2019t be afraid. I am here to
        help you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though you are a lowly worm, O Jacob,\n\tdon\u2019t be afraid, people
        of Israel, for I will help you.\n\tI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        your Redeemer.\n\tI am the Holy One of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be a new threshing instrument\n\twith many sharp teeth.\n\tYou
        will tear your enemies apart,\n\tmaking chaff of mountains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will toss them into the air,\n\tand the wind will blow them all
        away;\n\ta whirlwind will scatter them.\n\tThen you will rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tYou
        will glory in the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the poor and needy search for water and there is none,\n\tand
        their tongues are parched from thirst,\n\tthen I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        will answer them.\n\tI, the God of Israel, will never abandon them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will open up rivers for them on the high plateaus.\n\tI will give
        them fountains of water in the valleys.\n\tI will fill the desert with pools
        of water.\n\tRivers fed by springs will flow across the parched ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will plant trees in the barren desert\u2014\n\tcedar, acacia, myrtle,
        olive, cypress, fir, and pine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am doing this so all who see this miracle\n\twill understand what
        it means\u2014\n\tthat it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has done
        this,\n\tthe Holy One of Israel who created it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPresent the case for your idols,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CLet
        them show what they can do,\u201D\n\tsays the King of Israel.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the King of Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet them try to tell us what happened long ago\n\tso that we
        may consider the evidence.\n\tOr let them tell us what the future holds,\n\tso
        we can know what\u2019s going to happen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, tell us what will occur in the days ahead.\n\tThen we will know
        you are gods.\n\tIn fact, do anything\u2014good or bad!\n\tDo something that
