  - verses:
    - title: "Prediction of Babylon\u2019s Fall"
      content: "\u201CCome down, virgin daughter of Babylon, and sit in the dust.\n\tFor
        your days of sitting on a throne have ended.\n\tO daughter of Babylonia,[COMMENT[0]]
        never again will you be\n\tthe lovely princess, tender and delicate.  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Chaldea; '
        - ft: also in 47:5.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Take heavy millstones and grind flour.\n\tRemove your veil, and strip
        off your robe.\n\tExpose yourself to public view.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Bare your legs; pass through the rivers.
    - title: 
      content: "You will be naked and burdened with shame.\n\tI will take vengeance
        against you without pity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our Redeemer, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\n\tis the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO beautiful Babylon, sit now in darkness and silence.\n\tNever
        again will you be known as the queen of kingdoms.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I was angry with my chosen people\n\tand punished them by letting
        them fall into your hands.\n\tBut you, Babylon, showed them no mercy.\n\tYou
        oppressed even the elderly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018I will reign forever as queen of the world!\u2019\n\tYou
        did not reflect on your actions\n\tor think about their consequences.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to this, you pleasure-loving kingdom,\n\tliving at ease
        and feeling secure.\n\tYou say, \u2018I am the only one, and there is no
        other.\n\tI will never be a widow or lose my children.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well, both these things will come upon you in a moment:\n\twidowhood
        and the loss of your children.\n\tYes, these calamities will come upon you,\n\tdespite
        all your witchcraft and magic.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou felt secure in your wickedness.\n\t\u2018No one sees me,\u2019
        you said.\n\tBut your \u2018wisdom\u2019 and \u2018knowledge\u2019 have led
        you astray,\n\tand you said, \u2018I am the only one, and there is no other.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So disaster will overtake you,\n\tand you won\u2019t be able to charm
        it away.\n\tCalamity will fall upon you,\n\tand you won\u2019t be able to
        buy your way out.\n\tA catastrophe will strike you suddenly,\n\tone for which
        you are not prepared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow use your magical charms!\n\tUse the spells you have worked
        at all these years!\n\tMaybe they will do you some good.\n\tMaybe they can
        make someone afraid of you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the advice you receive has made you tired.\n\tWhere are all your
        astrologers,\n\tthose stargazers who make predictions each month?\n\tLet
        them stand up and save you from what the future holds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But they are like straw burning in a fire;\n\tthey cannot save themselves
        from the flame.\n\tYou will get no help from them at all;\n\ttheir hearth
        is no place to sit for warmth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And all your friends,\n\tthose with whom you\u2019ve done business
        since childhood,\n\twill go their own ways,\n\tturning a deaf ear to your
        cries."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Stubborn People"
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O family of Jacob,\n\tyou who are called by the
        name of Israel\n\tand born into the family of Judah.\n\tListen, you who take
        oaths in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand call on the God
        of Israel.\n\tYou don\u2019t keep your promises,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "even though you call yourself the holy city\n\tand talk about depending
        on the God of Israel,\n\twhose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Long ago I told you what was going to happen.\n\tThen suddenly I
        took action,\n\tand all my predictions came true.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I know how stubborn and obstinate you are.\n\tYour necks are
        as unbending as iron.\n\tYour heads are as hard as bronze.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why I told you what would happen;\n\tI told you beforehand
        what I was going to do.\n\tThen you could never say, \u2018My idols did it.\n\tMy
        wooden image and metal god commanded it to happen!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have heard my predictions and seen them fulfilled,\n\tbut you
        refuse to admit it.\n\tNow I will tell you new things,\n\tsecrets you have
        not yet heard.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are brand new, not things from the past.\n\tSo you cannot say,
        \u2018We knew that all the time!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, I will tell you of things that are entirely new,\n\tthings
        you never heard of before.\n\tFor I know so well what traitors you are.\n\tYou
        have been rebels from birth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet for my own sake and for the honor of my name,\n\tI will hold
        back my anger and not wipe you out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have refined you, but not as silver is refined.\n\tRather, I have
        refined you in the furnace of suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will rescue you for my sake\u2014\n\tyes, for my own sake!\n\tI
        will not let my reputation be tarnished,\n\tand I will not share my glory
        with idols!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Freedom from Babylon
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O family of Jacob,\n\tIsrael my chosen one!\n\tI
        alone am God,\n\tthe First and the Last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was my hand that laid the foundations of the earth,\n\tmy right
        hand that spread out the heavens above.\n\tWhen I call out the stars,\n\tthey
        all appear in order.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have any of your idols ever told you this?\n\tCome, all of you, and
        listen:\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen Cyrus as his ally.\n\tHe
        will use him to put an end to the empire of Babylon\n\tand to destroy the
        Babylonian[COMMENT[0]] armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Chaldean.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have said it: I am calling Cyrus!\n\tI will send him on this
        errand and will help him succeed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come closer, and listen to this.\n\tFrom the beginning I have told
        you plainly what would happen.\u201D\n\tAnd now the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and his Spirit\n\thave sent me with this message.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014\n\tyour Redeemer,
        the Holy One of Israel:\n\t\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God,\n\twho teaches you what is good for you\n\tand leads you along the paths
        you should follow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, that you had listened to my commands!\n\tThen you would have
        had peace flowing like a gentle river\n\tand righteousness rolling over you
        like waves in the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your descendants would have been like the sands along the seashore\u2014\n\ttoo
        many to count!\n\tThere would have been no need for your destruction,\n\tor
        for cutting off your family name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet even now, be free from your captivity!\n\tLeave Babylon and the
        Babylonians.[COMMENT[0]]Sing out this message!\n\tShout it to the ends of
        the earth!\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has redeemed his servants,\n\tthe
        people of Israel.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
