    - title: 
      content: "Sing for joy, O heavens!\n\tRejoice, O earth!\n\tBurst into song,
        O mountains!\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has comforted his people\n\tand
        will have compassion on them in their suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]] says, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has deserted us;\n\tthe Lord has forgotten us.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNever! Can a mother forget her nursing child?\n\tCan she feel
        no love for the child she has borne?\n\tBut even if that were possible,\n\tI
        would not forget you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, I have written your name on the palms of my hands.\n\tAlways
        in my mind is a picture of Jerusalem\u2019s walls in ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon your descendants will come back,\n\tand all who are trying to
        destroy you will go away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look around you and see,\n\tfor all your children will come back
        to you.\n\tAs surely as I live,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cthey
        will be like jewels or bridal ornaments for you to display.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven the most desolate parts of your abandoned land\n\twill
        soon be crowded with your people.\n\tYour enemies who enslaved you\n\twill
        be far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The generations born in exile will return and say,\n\t\u2018We need
        more room! It\u2019s crowded here!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will think to yourself,\n\t\u2018Who has given me all these
        descendants?\n\tFor most of my children were killed,\n\tand the rest were
        carried away into exile.\n\tI was left here all alone.\n\tWhere did all these
        people come from?\n\tWho bore these children?\n\tWho raised them for me?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CSee,
        I will give a signal to the godless nations.\n\tThey will carry your little
        sons back to you in their arms;\n\tthey will bring your daughters on their
        shoulders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Kings and queens will serve you\n\tand care for all your needs.\n\tThey
        will bow to the earth before you\n\tand lick the dust from your feet.\n\tThen
        you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tThose who
        trust in me will never be put to shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can snatch the plunder of war from the hands of a warrior?\n\tWho
        can demand that a tyrant[COMMENT[0]] let his captives go?  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls, Syriac version, and Latin Vulgate (also see
            49:25); Masoretic Text reads '
          body: a righteous person.
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\n\t\u201CThe captives of
        warriors will be released,\n\tand the plunder of tyrants will be retrieved.\n\tFor
        I will fight those who fight you,\n\tand I will save your children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will feed your enemies with their own flesh.\n\tThey will be drunk
        with rivers of their own blood.\n\tAll the world will know that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tam
        your Savior and your Redeemer,\n\tthe Mighty One of Israel.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D"
      comments:
