  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CWas your
        mother sent away because I divorced her?\n\tDid I sell you as slaves to my
        creditors?\n\tNo, you were sold because of your sins.\n\tAnd your mother,
        too, was taken because of your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why was no one there when I came?\n\tWhy didn\u2019t anyone answer
        when I called?\n\tIs it because I have no power to rescue?\n\tNo, that is
        not the reason!\n\tFor I can speak to the sea and make it dry up!\n\tI can
        turn rivers into deserts covered with dying fish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I dress the skies in darkness,\n\tcovering them with clothes of mourning.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Obedient Servant"
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given me his words
        of wisdom,\n\tso that I know how to comfort the weary.\n\tMorning by morning
        he wakens me\n\tand opens my understanding to his will.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken to me,\n\tand
        I have listened.\n\tI have not rebelled or turned away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I offered my back to those who beat me\n\tand my cheeks to those
        who pulled out my beard.\n\tI did not hide my face\n\tfrom mockery and spitting.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> helps me,\n\tI
        will not be disgraced.\n\tTherefore, I have set my face like a stone,\n\tdetermined
        to do his will.\n\tAnd I know that I will not be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He who gives me justice is near.\n\tWho will dare to bring charges
        against me now?\n\tWhere are my accusers?\n\tLet them appear!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is on my side!\n\tWho
        will declare me guilty?\n\tAll my enemies will be destroyed\n\tlike old clothes
        that have been eaten by moths!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who among you fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand obeys
        his servant?\n\tIf you are walking in darkness,\n\twithout a ray of light,\n\ttrust
        in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand rely on your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But watch out, you who live in your own light\n\tand warm yourselves
        by your own fires.\n\tThis is the reward you will receive from me:\n\tYou
        will soon fall down in great torment."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Lord
      content: "\u201CListen to me, all who hope for deliverance\u2014\n\tall who
        seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tConsider the rock from which
        you were cut,\n\tthe quarry from which you were mined.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, think about Abraham, your ancestor,\n\tand Sarah, who gave birth
        to your nation.\n\tAbraham was only one man when I called him.\n\tBut when
        I blessed him, he became a great nation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will comfort Israel[COMMENT[0]] again\n\tand
        have pity on her ruins.\n\tHer desert will blossom like Eden,\n\ther barren
        wilderness like the garden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tJoy
        and gladness will be found there.\n\tSongs of thanksgiving will fill the
        air.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Zion; '
        - ft: also in 51:16.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, my people.\n\tHear me, Israel,\n\tfor my law
        will be proclaimed,\n\tand my justice will become a light to the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My mercy and justice are coming soon.\n\tMy salvation is on the way.\n\tMy
        strong arm will bring justice to the nations.\n\tAll distant lands will look
        to me\n\tand wait in hope for my powerful arm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look up to the skies above,\n\tand gaze down on the earth below.\n\tFor
        the skies will disappear like smoke,\n\tand the earth will wear out like
        a piece of clothing.\n\tThe people of the earth will die like flies,\n\tbut
        my salvation lasts forever.\n\tMy righteous rule will never end!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you who know right from wrong,\n\tyou who cherish
        my law in your hearts.\n\tDo not be afraid of people\u2019s scorn,\n\tnor
        fear their insults.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the moth will devour them as it devours clothing.\n\tThe worm
        will eat at them as it eats wool.\n\tBut my righteousness will last forever.\n\tMy
        salvation will continue from generation to generation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wake up, wake up, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! Clothe yourself
        with strength!\n\tFlex your mighty right arm!\n\tRouse yourself as in the
        days of old\n\twhen you slew Egypt, the dragon of the Nile.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'You slew Rahab; you pierced the dragon. '
        - ft: Rahab is the name of a mythical sea monster that represents chaos in
            ancient literature. The name is used here as a poetic name for Egypt.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Are you not the same today,\n\tthe one who dried up the sea,\n\tmaking
        a path of escape through the depths\n\tso that your people could cross over?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who have been ransomed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        return.\n\tThey will enter Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]] singing,\n\tcrowned with
        everlasting joy.\n\tSorrow and mourning will disappear,\n\tand they will
        be filled with joy and gladness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, yes I, am the one who comforts you.\n\tSo why are you afraid
        of mere humans,\n\twho wither like the grass and disappear?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet you have forgotten the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, your
        Creator,\n\tthe one who stretched out the sky like a canopy\n\tand laid the
        foundations of the earth.\n\tWill you remain in constant dread of human oppressors?\n\tWill
        you continue to fear the anger of your enemies?\n\tWhere is their fury and
        anger now?\n\tIt is gone!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon all you captives will be released!\n\tImprisonment, starvation,
        and death will not be your fate!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\twho stirs up
        the sea, causing its waves to roar.\n\tMy name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I have put my words in your mouth\n\tand hidden you safely in
        my hand.\n\tI stretched out[COMMENT[0]] the sky like a canopy\n\tand laid
        the foundations of the earth.\n\tI am the one who says to Israel,\n\t\u2018You
        are my people!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Syriac version (see also 51:13); Hebrew reads '
          body: planted.
    - title: 
      content: "Wake up, wake up, O Jerusalem!\n\tYou have drunk the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        fury.\n\tYou have drunk the cup of terror,\n\ttipping out its last drops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Not one of your children is left alive\n\tto take your hand and guide
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These two calamities have fallen on you:\n\tdesolation and destruction,
        famine and war.\n\tAnd who is left to sympathize with you?\n\tWho is left
        to comfort you?[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek, Latin, and Syriac versions; Masoretic
            Text reads '
          body: How can I comfort you?
    - title: 
      content: "For your children have fainted and lie in the streets,\n\thelpless
        as antelopes caught in a net.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has poured
        out his fury;\n\tGod has rebuked them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now listen to this, you afflicted ones\n\twho sit in a drunken
        stupor,\n\tthough not from drinking wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tyour
        God and Defender, says:\n\t\u201CSee, I have taken the terrible cup from
        your hands.\n\tYou will drink no more of my fury.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, I will hand that cup to your tormentors,\n\tthose who said,
        \u2018We will trample you into the dust\n\tand walk on your backs.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Deliverance for Jerusalem
      content: "Wake up, wake up, O Zion!\n\tClothe yourself with strength.\n\tPut
        on your beautiful clothes, O holy city of Jerusalem,\n\tfor unclean and godless
        people will enter your gates no longer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rise from the dust, O Jerusalem.\n\tSit in a place of honor.\n\tRemove
        the chains of slavery from your neck,\n\tO captive daughter of Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CWhen
        I sold you into exile,\n\tI received no payment.\n\tNow I can redeem you\n\twithout
        having to pay for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CLong
        ago my people chose to live in Egypt. Now they are oppressed by Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What is this?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CWhy
        are my people enslaved again? Those who rule them shout in exultation.[COMMENT[0]]
        My name is blasphemed all day long.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:5a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Dead Sea Scrolls; Masoretic Text reads '
          body: Those who rule them wail.
      - number: '52:5b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'The Gentiles continually blaspheme my name because of you. '
        - ft: Compare Rom 2:24.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But I will reveal my name to my people, and they will come to know
        its power. Then at last they will recognize that I am the one who speaks
        to them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How beautiful on the mountains\n\tare the feet of the messenger who
        brings good news,\n\tthe good news of peace and salvation,\n\tthe news that
        the God of Israel[COMMENT[0]] reigns!  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "The watchmen shout and sing with joy,\n\tfor before their very eyes\n\tthey
        see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> returning to Jerusalem.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "Let the ruins of Jerusalem break into joyful song,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has comforted his people.\n\tHe has redeemed Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has demonstrated his holy power\n\tbefore
        the eyes of all the nations.\n\tAll the ends of the earth will see\n\tthe
        victory of our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get out! Get out and leave your captivity,\n\twhere everything you
        touch is unclean.\n\tGet out of there and purify yourselves,\n\tyou who carry
        home the sacred objects of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will not leave in a hurry,\n\trunning for your lives.\n\tFor
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will go ahead of you;\n\tyes, the God of
        Israel will protect you from behind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Suffering Servant"
      content: "See, my servant will prosper;\n\the will be highly exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But many were amazed when they saw him.[COMMENT[0]]His face was so
        disfigured he seemed hardly human,\n\tand from his appearance, one would
        scarcely know he was a man.  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads '
          body: you.
    - title: 
      content: "And he will startle[COMMENT[0]] many nations.\n\tKings will stand
        speechless in his presence.\n\tFor they will see what they had not been told;\n\tthey
        will understand what they had not heard about.[COMMENT[1]]"
      comments:
