  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Who has believed our message?\n\tTo whom has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        revealed his powerful arm?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My servant grew up in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence like a tender green shoot,\n\tlike a root in dry ground.\n\tThere
        was nothing beautiful or majestic about his appearance,\n\tnothing to attract
        us to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was despised and rejected\u2014\n\ta man of sorrows, acquainted
        with deepest grief.\n\tWe turned our backs on him and looked the other way.\n\tHe
        was despised, and we did not care.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet it was our weaknesses he carried;\n\tit was our sorrows[COMMENT[0]]
        that weighed him down.\n\tAnd we thought his troubles were a punishment from
        God,\n\ta punishment for his own sins!  "
      comments:
      - number: '53:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Yet it was our sicknesses he carried; / it was our diseases.
    - title: 
      content: "But he was pierced for our rebellion,\n\tcrushed for our sins.\n\tHe
        was beaten so we could be whole.\n\tHe was whipped so we could be healed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All of us, like sheep, have strayed away.\n\tWe have left God\u2019s
        paths to follow our own.\n\tYet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> laid on him\n\tthe
        sins of us all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was oppressed and treated harshly,\n\tyet he never said a word.\n\tHe
        was led like a lamb to the slaughter.\n\tAnd as a sheep is silent before
        the shearers,\n\the did not open his mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Unjustly condemned,\n\the was led away.[COMMENT[0]]No one cared that
        he died without descendants,\n\tthat his life was cut short in midstream.[COMMENT[1]]But
        he was struck down\n\tfor the rebellion of my people.  "
      comments:
      - number: '53:8a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'He was humiliated and received no justice. '
        - ft: Compare Acts 8:33.
          body: 
      - number: '53:8b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'As for his contemporaries, / who cared that his life was cut short
            in midstream? '
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'Who can speak of his descendants? / For his life was taken from
            the earth. '
        - ft: Compare Acts 8:33.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "He had done no wrong\n\tand had never deceived anyone.\n\tBut he
        was buried like a criminal;\n\the was put in a rich man\u2019s grave.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But it was the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s good plan to
        crush him\n\tand cause him grief.\n\tYet when his life is made an offering
        for sin,\n\the will have many descendants.\n\tHe will enjoy a long life,\n\tand
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s good plan will prosper in his
        hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he sees all that is accomplished by his anguish,\n\the will
        be satisfied.\n\tAnd because of his experience,\n\tmy righteous servant will
        make it possible\n\tfor many to be counted righteous,\n\tfor he will bear
        all their sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give him the honors of a victorious soldier,\n\tbecause he
        exposed himself to death.\n\tHe was counted among the rebels.\n\tHe bore
        the sins of many and interceded for rebels."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Future Glory for Jerusalem
      content: "\u201CSing, O childless woman,\n\tyou who have never given birth!\n\tBreak
        into loud and joyful song, O Jerusalem,\n\tyou who have never been in labor.\n\tFor
        the desolate woman now has more children\n\tthan the woman who lives with
        her husband,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEnlarge your house; build an addition.\n\tSpread out your home,
        and spare no expense!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you will soon be bursting at the seams.\n\tYour descendants will
        occupy other nations\n\tand resettle the ruined cities.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFear not; you will no longer live in shame.\n\tDon\u2019t be
        afraid; there is no more disgrace for you.\n\tYou will no longer remember
        the shame of your youth\n\tand the sorrows of widowhood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For your Creator will be your husband;\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!\n\tHe is your Redeemer, the Holy One
        of Israel,\n\tthe God of all the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has called you back from your
        grief\u2014\n\tas though you were a young wife abandoned by her husband,\u201D\n\tsays
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor a brief moment I abandoned you,\n\tbut with great compassion
        I will take you back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In a burst of anger I turned my face away for a little while.\n\tBut
        with everlasting love I will have compassion on you,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        your Redeemer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust as I swore in the time of Noah\n\tthat I would never again
        let a flood cover the earth,\n\tso now I swear\n\tthat I will never again
        be angry and punish you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the mountains may move\n\tand the hills disappear,\n\tbut even
        then my faithful love for you will remain.\n\tMy covenant of blessing will
        never be broken,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, who has
        mercy on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO storm-battered city,\n\ttroubled and desolate!\n\tI will
        rebuild you with precious jewels\n\tand make your foundations from lapis
        lazuli.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make your towers of sparkling rubies,\n\tyour gates of shining
        gems,\n\tand your walls of precious stones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will teach all your children,\n\tand they will enjoy great peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be secure under a government that is just and fair.\n\tYour
        enemies will stay far away.\n\tYou will live in peace,\n\tand terror will
        not come near.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If any nation comes to fight you,\n\tit is not because I sent them.\n\tWhoever
        attacks you will go down in defeat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have created the blacksmith\n\twho fans the coals beneath
        the forge\n\tand makes the weapons of destruction.\n\tAnd I have created
        the armies that destroy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But in that coming day\n\tno weapon turned against you will succeed.\n\tYou
        will silence every voice\n\traised up to accuse you.\n\tThese benefits are
        enjoyed by the servants of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t;\n\ttheir
        vindication will come from me.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Salvation"
      content: "\u201CIs anyone thirsty?\n\tCome and drink\u2014\n\teven if you have
        no money!\n\tCome, take your choice of wine or milk\u2014\n\tit\u2019s all
        free!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why spend your money on food that does not give you strength?\n\tWhy
        pay for food that does you no good?\n\tListen to me, and you will eat what
        is good.\n\tYou will enjoy the finest food.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome to me with your ears wide open.\n\tListen, and you will
        find life.\n\tI will make an everlasting covenant with you.\n\tI will give
        you all the unfailing love I promised to David.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See how I used him to display my power among the peoples.\n\tI made
        him a leader among the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You also will command nations you do not know,\n\tand peoples unknown
        to you will come running to obey,\n\tbecause I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,\n\tthe Holy One of Israel, have made you glorious.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> while you can find him.\n\tCall
        on him now while he is near.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let the wicked change their ways\n\tand banish the very thought of
        doing wrong.\n\tLet them turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he
        may have mercy on them.\n\tYes, turn to our God, for he will forgive generously.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy thoughts are nothing like your thoughts,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CAnd my ways are far beyond anything
        you could imagine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For just as the heavens are higher than the earth,\n\tso my ways
        are higher than your ways\n\tand my thoughts higher than your thoughts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe rain and snow come down from the heavens\n\tand stay on
        the ground to water the earth.\n\tThey cause the grain to grow,\n\tproducing
        seed for the farmer\n\tand bread for the hungry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is the same with my word.\n\tI send it out, and it always produces
        fruit.\n\tIt will accomplish all I want it to,\n\tand it will prosper everywhere
        I send it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will live in joy and peace.\n\tThe mountains and hills will burst
        into song,\n\tand the trees of the field will clap their hands!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where once there were thorns, cypress trees will grow.\n\tWhere nettles
        grew, myrtles will sprout up.\n\tThese events will bring great honor to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s name;\n\tthey will be an everlasting
        sign of his power and love.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Blessings for All Nations
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CBe just
        and fair to all.\n\tDo what is right and good,\n\tfor I am coming soon to
        rescue you\n\tand to display my righteousness among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Blessed are all those\n\twho are careful to do this.\n\tBlessed are
        those who honor my Sabbath days of rest\n\tand keep themselves from doing
        wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t let foreigners who commit themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        say,\n\t\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will never let me be part of
        his people.\u2019\n\tAnd don\u2019t let the eunuchs say,\n\t\u2018I\u2019m
        a dried-up tree with no children and no future.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\tI will
        bless those eunuchs\n\twho keep my Sabbath days holy\n\tand who choose to
        do what pleases me\n\tand commit their lives to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give them\u2014within the walls of my house\u2014\n\ta memorial
        and a name\n\tfar greater than sons and daughters could give.\n\tFor the
        name I give them is an everlasting one.\n\tIt will never disappear!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will also bless the foreigners who commit themselves to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\twho serve him and love his name,\n\twho
        worship him and do not desecrate the Sabbath day of rest,\n\tand who hold
        fast to my covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will bring them to my holy mountain of Jerusalem\n\tand will fill
        them with joy in my house of prayer.\n\tI will accept their burnt offerings
        and sacrifices,\n\tbecause my Temple will be called a house of prayer for
        all nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\twho brings
        back the outcasts of Israel, says:\n\tI will bring others, too,\n\tbesides
        my people Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Sinful Leaders Condemned
      content: "Come, wild animals of the field!\n\tCome, wild animals of the forest!\n\tCome
        and devour my people!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the leaders of my people\u2014\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        watchmen, his shepherds\u2014\n\tare blind and ignorant.\n\tThey are like
        silent watchdogs\n\tthat give no warning when danger comes.\n\tThey love
        to lie around, sleeping and dreaming.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like greedy dogs, they are never satisfied.\n\tThey are ignorant
        shepherds,\n\tall following their own path\n\tand intent on personal gain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome,\u201D they say, \u201Clet\u2019s get some wine and have
        a party.\n\tLet\u2019s all get drunk.\n\tThen tomorrow we\u2019ll do it again\n\tand
        have an even bigger party!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Good people pass away;\n\tthe godly often die before their time.\n\tBut
        no one seems to care or wonder why.\n\tNo one seems to understand\n\tthat
        God is protecting them from the evil to come.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For those who follow godly paths\n\twill rest in peace when they
        die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Idolatrous Worship Condemned
      content: "\u201CBut you\u2014come here, you witches\u2019 children,\n\tyou
        offspring of adulterers and prostitutes!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whom do you mock,\n\tmaking faces and sticking out your tongues?\n\tYou
        children of sinners and liars!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You worship your idols with great passion\n\tbeneath the oaks and
        under every green tree.\n\tYou sacrifice your children down in the valleys,\n\tamong
        the jagged rocks in the cliffs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your gods are the smooth stones in the valleys.\n\tYou worship them
        with liquid offerings and grain offerings.\n\tThey, not I, are your inheritance.\n\tDo
        you think all this makes me happy?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have committed adultery on every high mountain.\n\tThere you
        have worshiped idols\n\tand have been unfaithful to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have put pagan symbols\n\ton your doorposts and behind your doors.\n\tYou
        have left me\n\tand climbed into bed with these detestable gods.\n\tYou have
        committed yourselves to them.\n\tYou love to look at their naked bodies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have gone to Molech[COMMENT[0]]with olive oil and many perfumes,\n\tsending
        your agents far and wide,\n\teven to the world of the dead.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '57:9a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to the king.
      - number: '57:9b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "You grew weary in your search,\n\tbut you never gave up.\n\tDesire
        gave you renewed strength,\n\tand you did not grow weary.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAre you afraid of these idols?\n\tDo they terrify you?\n\tIs
        that why you have lied to me\n\tand forgotten me and my words?\n\tIs it because
        of my long silence\n\tthat you no longer fear me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I will expose your so-called good deeds.\n\tNone of them will
        help you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let\u2019s see if your idols can save you\n\twhen you cry to them
        for help.\n\tWhy, a puff of wind can knock them down!\n\tIf you just breathe
        on them, they fall over!\n\tBut whoever trusts in me will inherit the land\n\tand
        possess my holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: God Forgives the Repentant
      content: "God says, \u201CRebuild the road!\n\tClear away the rocks and stones\n\tso
        my people can return from captivity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The high and lofty one who lives in eternity,\n\tthe Holy One, says
        this:\n\t\u201CI live in the high and holy place\n\twith those whose spirits
        are contrite and humble.\n\tI restore the crushed spirit of the humble\n\tand
        revive the courage of those with repentant hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will not fight against you forever;\n\tI will not always be
        angry.\n\tIf I were, all people would pass away\u2014\n\tall the souls I
        have made.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was angry,\n\tso I punished these greedy people.\n\tI withdrew
        from them,\n\tbut they kept going on their own stubborn way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have seen what they do,\n\tbut I will heal them anyway!\n\tI will
        lead them.\n\tI will comfort those who mourn,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "bringing words of praise to their lips.\n\tMay they have abundant
        peace, both near and far,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        who heals them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut those who still reject me are like the restless sea,\n\twhich
        is never still\n\tbut continually churns up mud and dirt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is no peace for the wicked,\u201D\n\tsays my God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: True and False Worship
      content: "\u201CShout with the voice of a trumpet blast.\n\tShout aloud! Don\u2019t
        be timid.\n\tTell my people Israel[COMMENT[0]] of their sins!  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Yet they act so pious!\n\tThey come to the Temple every day\n\tand
        seem delighted to learn all about me.\n\tThey act like a righteous nation\n\tthat
        would never abandon the laws of its God.\n\tThey ask me to take action on
        their behalf,\n\tpretending they want to be near me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018We have fasted before you!\u2019 they say.\n\t\u2018Why aren\u2019t
        you impressed?\n\tWe have been very hard on ourselves,\n\tand you don\u2019t
        even notice it!\u2019\n\t\u201CI will tell you why!\u201D I respond.\n\t\u201CIt\u2019s
        because you are fasting to please yourselves.\n\tEven while you fast,\n\tyou
        keep oppressing your workers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What good is fasting\n\twhen you keep on fighting and quarreling?\n\tThis
        kind of fasting\n\twill never get you anywhere with me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You humble yourselves\n\tby going through the motions of penance,\n\tbowing
        your heads\n\tlike reeds bending in the wind.\n\tYou dress in burlap\n\tand
        cover yourselves with ashes.\n\tIs this what you call fasting?\n\tDo you
        really think this will please the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo, this is the kind of fasting I want:\n\tFree those who are
        wrongly imprisoned;\n\tlighten the burden of those who work for you.\n\tLet
        the oppressed go free,\n\tand remove the chains that bind people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Share your food with the hungry,\n\tand give shelter to the homeless.\n\tGive
        clothes to those who need them,\n\tand do not hide from relatives who need
        your help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen your salvation will come like the dawn,\n\tand your wounds
        will quickly heal.\n\tYour godliness will lead you forward,\n\tand the glory
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect you from behind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then when you call, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will answer.\n\t\u2018Yes,
        I am here,\u2019 he will quickly reply.\n\t\u201CRemove the heavy yoke of
        oppression.\n\tStop pointing your finger and spreading vicious rumors!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Feed the hungry,\n\tand help those in trouble.\n\tThen your light
        will shine out from the darkness,\n\tand the darkness around you will be
        as bright as noon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will guide you continually,\n\tgiving
        you water when you are dry\n\tand restoring your strength.\n\tYou will be
        like a well-watered garden,\n\tlike an ever-flowing spring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Some of you will rebuild the deserted ruins of your cities.\n\tThen
        you will be known as a rebuilder of walls\n\tand a restorer of homes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CKeep the Sabbath day holy.\n\tDon\u2019t pursue your own interests
        on that day,\n\tbut enjoy the Sabbath\n\tand speak of it with delight as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s holy day.\n\tHonor the Sabbath
        in everything you do on that day,\n\tand don\u2019t follow your own desires
        or talk idly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be your delight.\n\tI will
        give you great honor\n\tand satisfy you with the inheritance I promised to
        your ancestor Jacob.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Warnings against Sin
      content: "Listen! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s arm is not too
        weak to save you,\n\tnor is his ear too deaf to hear you call.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s your sins that have cut you off from God.\n\tBecause of
        your sins, he has turned away\n\tand will not listen anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your hands are the hands of murderers,\n\tand your fingers are filthy
        with sin.\n\tYour lips are full of lies,\n\tand your mouth spews corruption.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one cares about being fair and honest.\n\tThe people\u2019s lawsuits
        are based on lies.\n\tThey conceive evil deeds\n\tand then give birth to
        sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They hatch deadly snakes\n\tand weave spiders\u2019 webs.\n\tWhoever
        eats their eggs will die;\n\twhoever cracks them will hatch a viper.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their webs can\u2019t be made into clothing,\n\tand nothing they
        do is productive.\n\tAll their activity is filled with sin,\n\tand violence
        is their trademark.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their feet run to do evil,\n\tand they rush to commit murder.\n\tThey
        think only about sinning.\n\tMisery and destruction always follow them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They don\u2019t know where to find peace\n\tor what it means to be
        just and good.\n\tThey have mapped out crooked roads,\n\tand no one who follows
        them knows a moment\u2019s peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So there is no justice among us,\n\tand we know nothing about right
        living.\n\tWe look for light but find only darkness.\n\tWe look for bright
        skies but walk in gloom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We grope like the blind along a wall,\n\tfeeling our way like people
        without eyes.\n\tEven at brightest noontime,\n\twe stumble as though it were
        dark.\n\tAmong the living,\n\twe are like the dead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We growl like hungry bears;\n\twe moan like mournful doves.\n\tWe
        look for justice, but it never comes.\n\tWe look for rescue, but it is far
        away from us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For our sins are piled up before God\n\tand testify against us.\n\tYes,
        we know what sinners we are.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We know we have rebelled and have denied the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tWe
        have turned our backs on our God.\n\tWe know how unfair and oppressive we
        have been,\n\tcarefully planning our deceitful lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our courts oppose the righteous,\n\tand justice is nowhere to be
        found.\n\tTruth stumbles in the streets,\n\tand honesty has been outlawed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, truth is gone,\n\tand anyone who renounces evil is attacked.\n\tThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looked and was displeased\n\tto find there was
        no justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was amazed to see that no one intervened\n\tto help the oppressed.\n\tSo
        he himself stepped in to save them with his strong arm,\n\tand his justice
        sustained him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He put on righteousness as his body armor\n\tand placed the helmet
        of salvation on his head.\n\tHe clothed himself with a robe of vengeance\n\tand
        wrapped himself in a cloak of divine passion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will repay his enemies for their evil deeds.\n\tHis fury will
        fall on his foes.\n\tHe will pay them back even to the ends of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the west, people will respect the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t;\n\tin
        the east, they will glorify him.\n\tFor he will come like a raging flood
        tide\n\tdriven by the breath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '59:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'When the enemy comes like a raging flood tide, / the Spirit of the '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Redeemer will come to Jerusalem\n\tto buy back those in
        Israel\n\twho have turned from their sins,\u201D[COMMENT[0]]says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '59:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'The Redeemer will come to Zion / to buy back those in Jacob / who
            have turned from their sins. '
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'The one who rescues will come on behalf of Zion, / and he will turn
            Jacob away from ungodliness. '
