      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Future Glory for Jerusalem
      content: "\u201CArise, Jerusalem! Let your light shine for all to see.\n\tFor
        the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises to shine on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Darkness as black as night covers all the nations of the earth,\n\tbut
        the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises and appears over you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All nations will come to your light;\n\tmighty kings will come to
        see your radiance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook and see, for everyone is coming home!\n\tYour sons are
        coming from distant lands;\n\tyour little daughters will be carried home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your eyes will shine,\n\tand your heart will thrill with joy,\n\tfor
        merchants from around the world will come to you.\n\tThey will bring you
        the wealth of many lands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Vast caravans of camels will converge on you,\n\tthe camels of Midian
        and Ephah.\n\tThe people of Sheba will bring gold and frankincense\n\tand
        will come worshiping the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The flocks of Kedar will be given to you,\n\tand the rams of Nebaioth
        will be brought for my altars.\n\tI will accept their offerings,\n\tand I
        will make my Temple glorious.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd what do I see flying like clouds to Israel,\n\tlike doves
        to their nests?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are ships from the ends of the earth,\n\tfrom lands that trust
        in me,\n\tled by the great ships of Tarshish.\n\tThey are bringing the people
        of Israel home from far away,\n\tcarrying their silver and gold.\n\tThey
        will honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\tthe Holy One of Israel,\n\tfor
        he has filled you with splendor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CForeigners will come to rebuild your towns,\n\tand their kings
        will serve you.\n\tFor though I have destroyed you in my anger,\n\tI will
        now have mercy on you through my grace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your gates will stay open day and night\n\tto receive the wealth
        of many lands.\n\tThe kings of the world will be led as captives\n\tin a
        victory procession.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the nations that refuse to serve you\n\twill be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe glory of Lebanon will be yours\u2014\n\tthe forests of
        cypress, fir, and pine\u2014\n\tto beautify my sanctuary.\n\tMy Temple will
        be glorious!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The descendants of your tormentors\n\twill come and bow before you.\n\tThose
        who despised you\n\twill kiss your feet.\n\tThey will call you the City of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tand Zion of the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThough you were once despised and hated,\n\twith no one traveling
        through you,\n\tI will make you beautiful forever,\n\ta joy to all generations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Powerful kings and mighty nations\n\twill satisfy your every need,\n\tas
        though you were a child\n\tnursing at the breast of a queen.\n\tYou will
        know at last that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tam your Savior
        and your Redeemer,\n\tthe Mighty One of Israel.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '60:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'of Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will exchange your bronze for gold,\n\tyour iron for silver,\n\tyour
        wood for bronze,\n\tand your stones for iron.\n\tI will make peace your leader\n\tand
        righteousness your ruler.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Violence will disappear from your land;\n\tthe desolation and destruction
        of war will end.\n\tSalvation will surround you like city walls,\n\tand praise
        will be on the lips of all who enter there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo longer will you need the sun to shine by day,\n\tnor the
        moon to give its light by night,\n\tfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God will be your everlasting light,\n\tand your God will be your glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your sun will never set;\n\tyour moon will not go down.\n\tFor the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be your everlasting light.\n\tYour days
        of mourning will come to an end.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All your people will be righteous.\n\tThey will possess their land
        forever,\n\tfor I will plant them there with my own hands\n\tin order to
        bring myself glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The smallest family will become a thousand people,\n\tand the tiniest
        group will become a mighty nation.\n\tAt the right time, I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        will make it happen.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Good News for the Oppressed
      content: "The Spirit of the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is upon me,\n\tfor
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has anointed me\n\tto bring good news to
        the poor.\n\tHe has sent me to comfort the brokenhearted\n\tand to proclaim
        that captives will be released\n\tand prisoners will be freed.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
