        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Tell the daughter of Zion.
    - title: 
      content: "They will be called \u201CThe Holy People\u201D\n\tand \u201CThe
        People Redeemed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D\n\tAnd Jerusalem
        will be known as \u201CThe Desirable Place\u201D\n\tand \u201CThe City No
        Longer Forsaken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Enemies"
      content: "Who is this who comes from Edom,\n\tfrom the city of Bozrah,\n\twith
        his clothing stained red?\n\tWho is this in royal robes,\n\tmarching in his
        great strength?\n\t\u201CIt is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, announcing
        your salvation!\n\tIt is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, who has
        the power to save!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why are your clothes so red,\n\tas if you have been treading out
        grapes?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have been treading the winepress alone;\n\tno one was there
        to help me.\n\tIn my anger I have trampled my enemies\n\tas if they were
        grapes.\n\tIn my fury I have trampled my foes.\n\tTheir blood has stained
        my clothes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the time has come for me to avenge my people,\n\tto ransom them
        from their oppressors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was amazed to see that no one intervened\n\tto help the oppressed.\n\tSo
        I myself stepped in to save them with my strong arm,\n\tand my wrath sustained
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I crushed the nations in my anger\n\tand made them stagger and fall
        to the ground,\n\tspilling their blood upon the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Praise for Deliverance
      content: "I will tell of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s unfailing
        love.\n\tI will praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for all he has done.\n\tI
        will rejoice in his great goodness to Israel,\n\twhich he has granted according
        to his mercy and love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u201CThey are my very own people.\n\tSurely they will not
        betray me again.\u201D\n\tAnd he became their Savior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In all their suffering he also suffered,\n\tand he personally[COMMENT[0]]
        rescued them.\n\tIn his love and mercy he redeemed them.\n\tHe lifted them
        up and carried them\n\tthrough all the years.  "
      comments:
      - number: '63:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: and the angel of his presence.
    - title: 
      content: "But they rebelled against him\n\tand grieved his Holy Spirit.\n\tSo
        he became their enemy\n\tand fought against them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they remembered those days of old\n\twhen Moses led his people
        out of Egypt.\n\tThey cried out, \u201CWhere is the one who brought Israel
        through the sea,\n\twith Moses as their shepherd?\n\tWhere is the one who
        sent his Holy Spirit\n\tto be among his people?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where is the one whose power was displayed\n\twhen Moses lifted up
        his hand\u2014\n\tthe one who divided the sea before them,\n\tmaking himself
        famous forever?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where is the one who led them through the bottom of the sea?\n\tThey
        were like fine stallions\n\tracing through the desert, never stumbling.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As with cattle going down into a peaceful valley,\n\tthe Spirit of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them rest.\n\tYou led your people, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tand
        gained a magnificent reputation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Prayer for Mercy and Pardon
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, look down from heaven;\n\tlook
        from your holy, glorious home, and see us.\n\tWhere is the passion and the
        might\n\tyou used to show on our behalf?\n\tWhere are your mercy and compassion
        now?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Surely you are still our Father!\n\tEven if Abraham and Jacob[COMMENT[0]]
        would disown us,  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you would still be our
        Father.\n\tYou are our Redeemer from ages past.  "
      comments:
      - number: '63:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Israel. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, why have you allowed us to turn
        from your path?\n\tWhy have you given us stubborn hearts so we no longer
        fear you?\n\tReturn and help us, for we are your servants,\n\tthe tribes
        that are your special possession.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How briefly your holy people possessed your holy place,\n\tand now
        our enemies have destroyed it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sometimes it seems as though we never belonged to you,\n\tas though
        we had never been known as your people."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]Oh, that you would burst from the heavens and come
        down!\n\tHow the mountains would quake in your presence!  "
