    - title: 
      content: "When you came down long ago,\n\tyou did awesome deeds beyond our
        highest expectations.\n\tAnd oh, how the mountains quaked!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For since the world began,\n\tno ear has heard\n\tand no eye has
        seen a God like you,\n\twho works for those who wait for him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You welcome those who gladly do good,\n\twho follow godly ways.\n\tBut
        you have been very angry with us,\n\tfor we are not godly.\n\tWe are constant
        sinners;\n\thow can people like us be saved?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We are all infected and impure with sin.\n\tWhen we display our righteous
        deeds,\n\tthey are nothing but filthy rags.\n\tLike autumn leaves, we wither
        and fall,\n\tand our sins sweep us away like the wind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet no one calls on your name\n\tor pleads with you for mercy.\n\tTherefore,
        you have turned away from us\n\tand turned us over[COMMENT[0]] to our sins.  "
      comments:
      - number: '64:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek, Syriac, and Aramaic versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: melted us.
    - title: 
      content: "And yet, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you are our Father.\n\tWe
        are the clay, and you are the potter.\n\tWe all are formed by your hand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be so angry with us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tPlease
        don\u2019t remember our sins forever.\n\tLook at us, we pray,\n\tand see
        that we are all your people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your holy cities are destroyed.\n\tZion is a wilderness;\n\tyes,
        Jerusalem is a desolate ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The holy and beautiful Temple\n\twhere our ancestors praised you\n\thas
        been burned down,\n\tand all the things of beauty are destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After all this, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, must you still refuse
        to help us?\n\tWill you continue to be silent and punish us?"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment and Final Salvation
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\n\t\u201CI was ready to respond,
        but no one asked for help.\n\tI was ready to be found, but no one was looking
        for me.\n\tI said, \u2018Here I am, here I am!\u2019\n\tto a nation that
        did not call on my name.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to a nation that did not bear my name.
    - title: 
      content: "All day long I opened my arms to a rebellious people.[COMMENT[0]]But
        they follow their own evil paths\n\tand their own crooked schemes.  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:1-2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'I was found by people who were not looking for me. / I showed myself
            to those who were not asking for me. / All day long I opened my arms
            to them, / but they were disobedient and rebellious. '
        - ft: Compare Rom 10:20-21.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "All day long they insult me to my face\n\tby worshiping idols in
        their sacred gardens.\n\tThey burn incense on pagan altars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At night they go out among the graves,\n\tworshiping the dead.\n\tThey
        eat the flesh of pigs\n\tand make stews with other forbidden foods.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet they say to each other,\n\t\u2018Don\u2019t come too close or
        you will defile me!\n\tI am holier than you!\u2019\n\tThese people are a
        stench in my nostrils,\n\tan acrid smell that never goes away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, my decree is written out[COMMENT[0]] in front of me:\n\tI
        will not stand silent;\n\tI will repay them in full!\n\tYes, I will repay
        them\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'their sins are written out; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: it stands written.
    - title: 
      content: "both for their own sins\n\tand for those of their ancestors,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor they also burned incense
        on the mountains\n\tand insulted me on the hills.\n\tI will pay them back
        in full!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I will not destroy them all,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor
        just as good grapes are found among a cluster of bad ones\n\t(and someone
        will say, \u2018Don\u2019t throw them all away\u2014\n\tsome of those grapes
        are good!\u2019),\n\tso I will not destroy all Israel.\n\tFor I still have
        true servants there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will preserve a remnant of the people of Israel[COMMENT[0]]and
        of Judah to possess my land.\n\tThose I choose will inherit it,\n\tand my
        servants will live there.  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'remnant of Jacob. '
        - ft: See note on 14:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The plain of Sharon will again be filled with flocks\n\tfor my people
        who have searched for me,\n\tand the valley of Achor will be a place to pasture
        herds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut because the rest of you have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tand
        have forgotten his Temple,\n\tand because you have prepared feasts to honor
        the god of Fate\n\tand have offered mixed wine to the god of Destiny,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "now I will \u2018destine\u2019 you for the sword.\n\tAll of you will
        bow down before the executioner.\n\tFor when I called, you did not answer.\n\tWhen
        I spoke, you did not listen.\n\tYou deliberately sinned\u2014before my very
        eyes\u2014\n\tand chose to do what you know I despise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\n\t\u201CMy servants will eat,\n\tbut you will starve.\n\tMy servants
        will drink,\n\tbut you will be thirsty.\n\tMy servants will rejoice,\n\tbut
        you will be sad and ashamed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My servants will sing for joy,\n\tbut you will cry in sorrow and
        despair.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your name will be a curse word among my people,\n\tfor the Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy you\n\tand will call his true servants
        by another name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who invoke a blessing or take an oath\n\twill do so by the God
        of truth.\n\tFor I will put aside my anger\n\tand forget the evil of earlier
        days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook! I am creating new heavens and a new earth,\n\tand no
        one will even think about the old ones anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Be glad; rejoice forever in my creation!\n\tAnd look! I will create
        Jerusalem as a place of happiness.\n\tHer people will be a source of joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will rejoice over Jerusalem\n\tand delight in my people.\n\tAnd
        the sound of weeping and crying\n\twill be heard in it no more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo longer will babies die when only a few days old.\n\tNo longer
        will adults die before they have lived a full life.\n\tNo longer will people
        be considered old at one hundred!\n\tOnly the cursed will die that young!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In those days people will live in the houses they build\n\tand eat
        the fruit of their own vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Unlike the past, invaders will not take their houses\n\tand confiscate
        their vineyards.\n\tFor my people will live as long as trees,\n\tand my chosen
        ones will have time to enjoy their hard-won gains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will not work in vain,\n\tand their children will not be doomed
        to misfortune.\n\tFor they are people blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tand
        their children, too, will be blessed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will answer them before they even call to me.\n\tWhile they are
        still talking about their needs,\n\tI will go ahead and answer their prayers!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wolf and the lamb will feed together.\n\tThe lion will eat hay
        like a cow.\n\tBut the snakes will eat dust.\n\tIn those days no one will
        be hurt or destroyed on my holy mountain.\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CHeaven
        is my throne,\n\tand the earth is my footstool.\n\tCould you build me a temple
        as good as that?\n\tCould you build me such a resting place?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My hands have made both heaven and earth;\n\tthey and everything
        in them are mine.[COMMENT[0]]I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have
        spoken!\n\t\u201CI will bless those who have humble and contrite hearts,\n\twho
        tremble at my word.  "
      comments:
      - number: '66:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek, Latin, and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: these things are.
    - title: 
      content: "But those who choose their own ways\u2014\n\tdelighting in their
        detestable sins\u2014\n\twill not have their offerings accepted.\n\tWhen
        such people sacrifice a bull,\n\tit is no more acceptable than a human sacrifice.\n\tWhen
        they sacrifice a lamb,\n\tit\u2019s as though they had sacrificed a dog!\n\tWhen
        they bring an offering of grain,\n\tthey might as well offer the blood of
        a pig.\n\tWhen they burn frankincense,\n\tit\u2019s as if they had blessed
        an idol.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will send them great trouble\u2014\n\tall the things they feared.\n\tFor
        when I called, they did not answer.\n\tWhen I spoke, they did not listen.\n\tThey
        deliberately sinned before my very eyes\n\tand chose to do what they know
        I despise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tall
        you who tremble at his words:\n\t\u201CYour own people hate you\n\tand throw
        you out for being loyal to my name.\n\t\u2018Let the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        be honored!\u2019 they scoff.\n\t\u2018Be joyful in him!\u2019\n\tBut they
        will be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What is all the commotion in the city?\n\tWhat is that terrible noise
        from the Temple?\n\tIt is the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\ttaking
        vengeance against his enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBefore the birth pains even begin,\n\tJerusalem gives birth
        to a son.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has ever seen anything as strange as this?\n\tWho ever heard
        of such a thing?\n\tHas a nation ever been born in a single day?\n\tHas a
        country ever come forth in a mere moment?\n\tBut by the time Jerusalem\u2019s[COMMENT[0]]
        birth pains begin,\n\ther children will be born.  "
      comments:
      - number: '66:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "Zion\u2019s."
    - title: 
      content: "Would I ever bring this nation to the point of birth\n\tand then
        not deliver it?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CNo!
        I would never keep this nation from being born,\u201D\n\tsays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRejoice with Jerusalem!\n\tBe glad with her, all you who love
        her\n\tand all you who mourn for her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Drink deeply of her glory\n\teven as an infant drinks at its mother\u2019s
        comforting breasts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CI will
        give Jerusalem a river of peace and prosperity.\n\tThe wealth of the nations
        will flow to her.\n\tHer children will be nursed at her breasts,\n\tcarried
        in her arms, and held on her lap.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will comfort you there in Jerusalem\n\tas a mother comforts her
        child.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you see these things, your heart will rejoice.\n\tYou will flourish
        like the grass!\n\tEveryone will see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        hand of blessing on his servants\u2014\n\tand his anger against his enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming with fire,\n\tand
        his swift chariots roar like a whirlwind.\n\tHe will bring punishment with
        the fury of his anger\n\tand the flaming fire of his hot rebuke.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will punish the world by fire\n\tand
        by his sword.\n\tHe will judge the earth,\n\tand many will be killed by him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose who \u2018consecrate\u2019 and \u2018purify\u2019 themselves
        in a sacred garden with its idol in the center\u2014feasting on pork and
        rats and other detestable meats\u2014will come to a terrible end,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI can see what they are doing, and I know what they are thinking.
        So I will gather all nations and peoples together, and they will see my glory. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will perform a sign among them. And I will send those who survive
        to be messengers to the nations\u2014to Tarshish, to the Libyans[COMMENT[0]]
        and Lydians[COMMENT[1]] (who are famous as archers), to Tubal and Greece,[COMMENT[2]]
        and to all the lands beyond the sea that have not heard of my fame or seen
        my glory. There they will declare my glory to the nations. "
      comments:
